16 // Map of UR error codes to PI error codes
17 static pi_result ur2piResult(ur_result_t urResult) {
18  if (urResult == UR_RESULT_SUCCESS)
19  return PI_SUCCESS;
20 
21  switch (urResult) {
22  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION:
23  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION;
24  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_QUEUE_PROPERTIES:
25  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_QUEUE_PROPERTIES;
26  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_QUEUE:
27  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_QUEUE;
28  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE:
29  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE;
30  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_CONTEXT:
31  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_CONTEXT;
32  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_PLATFORM:
33  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_PLATFORM;
34  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_BINARY:
35  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_BINARY;
36  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_PROGRAM:
37  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_PROGRAM;
38  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_SAMPLER:
39  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_SAMPLER;
40  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_MEM_OBJECT:
41  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_MEM_OBJECT;
42  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_EVENT:
43  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_EVENT;
44  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_EVENT_WAIT_LIST:
45  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_EVENT_WAIT_LIST;
46  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_MISALIGNED_SUB_BUFFER_OFFSET:
47  return PI_ERROR_MISALIGNED_SUB_BUFFER_OFFSET;
48  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_WORK_GROUP_SIZE:
49  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_WORK_GROUP_SIZE;
50  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_COMPILER_NOT_AVAILABLE:
51  return PI_ERROR_COMPILER_NOT_AVAILABLE;
52  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_PROFILING_INFO_NOT_AVAILABLE:
53  return PI_ERROR_PROFILING_INFO_NOT_AVAILABLE;
54  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_DEVICE_NOT_FOUND:
55  return PI_ERROR_DEVICE_NOT_FOUND;
56  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_DEVICE:
57  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_DEVICE;
58  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_DEVICE_REQUIRES_RESET:
59  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_DEVICE_LOST:
60  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_DEVICE_NOT_AVAILABLE:
61  return PI_ERROR_DEVICE_NOT_AVAILABLE;
62  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_DEVICE_PARTITION_FAILED:
63  return PI_ERROR_DEVICE_PARTITION_FAILED;
64  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_DEVICE_PARTITION_COUNT:
65  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_DEVICE_PARTITION_COUNT;
66  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_WORK_ITEM_SIZE:
67  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_WORK_ITEM_SIZE;
68  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_WORK_DIMENSION:
69  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_WORK_DIMENSION;
70  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_KERNEL_ARGS:
71  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_KERNEL_ARGS;
72  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_KERNEL:
73  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_KERNEL;
74  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_KERNEL_NAME:
75  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_KERNEL_NAME;
76  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_KERNEL_ARGUMENT_INDEX:
77  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_ARG_INDEX;
78  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_KERNEL_ARGUMENT_SIZE:
79  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_ARG_SIZE;
80  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_KERNEL_ATTRIBUTE_VALUE:
81  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE;
82  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_IMAGE_SIZE:
83  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_IMAGE_SIZE;
84  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_IMAGE_FORMAT_DESCRIPTOR:
85  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_IMAGE_FORMAT_DESCRIPTOR;
86  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_IMAGE_FORMAT_NOT_SUPPORTED:
87  return PI_ERROR_IMAGE_FORMAT_NOT_SUPPORTED;
88  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_MEM_OBJECT_ALLOCATION_FAILURE:
89  return PI_ERROR_MEM_OBJECT_ALLOCATION_FAILURE;
90  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_PROGRAM_EXECUTABLE:
91  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_PROGRAM_EXECUTABLE;
92  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_UNINITIALIZED:
93  return PI_ERROR_UNINITIALIZED;
94  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_OUT_OF_HOST_MEMORY:
95  return PI_ERROR_OUT_OF_HOST_MEMORY;
96  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_OUT_OF_DEVICE_MEMORY:
97  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_OUT_OF_RESOURCES:
98  return PI_ERROR_OUT_OF_RESOURCES;
99  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_PROGRAM_BUILD_FAILURE:
100  return PI_ERROR_BUILD_PROGRAM_FAILURE;
101  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_PROGRAM_LINK_FAILURE:
102  return PI_ERROR_LINK_PROGRAM_FAILURE;
103  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_VERSION:
104  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION;
105  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_FEATURE:
106  return PI_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_FEATURE;
107  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_ARGUMENT:
108  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_NULL_HANDLE:
109  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_HANDLE_OBJECT_IN_USE:
110  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_NULL_POINTER:
111  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE;
112  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_SIZE:
113  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_SIZE:
114  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_BUFFER_SIZE;
115  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_ALIGNMENT:
116  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE;
117  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_SYNCHRONIZATION_OBJECT:
118  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_ENUMERATION:
119  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_ENUMERATION:
120  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE;
121  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_IMAGE_FORMAT:
122  return PI_ERROR_IMAGE_FORMAT_NOT_SUPPORTED;
123  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_NATIVE_BINARY:
124  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_BINARY;
125  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_GLOBAL_NAME:
126  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE;
127  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_FUNCTION_NAME:
128  return PI_ERROR_FUNCTION_ADDRESS_IS_NOT_AVAILABLE;
129  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_GROUP_SIZE_DIMENSION:
130  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_WORK_DIMENSION;
131  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_GLOBAL_WIDTH_DIMENSION:
132  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE;
133  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_PROGRAM_UNLINKED:
134  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_PROGRAM_EXECUTABLE;
135  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_OVERLAPPING_REGIONS:
136  return PI_ERROR_MEM_COPY_OVERLAP;
137  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_HOST_PTR:
138  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_HOST_PTR;
139  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_USM_SIZE:
140  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_BUFFER_SIZE;
141  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_OBJECT_ALLOCATION_FAILURE:
142  return PI_ERROR_OUT_OF_RESOURCES;
143  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_ADAPTER_SPECIFIC:
144  return PI_ERROR_PLUGIN_SPECIFIC_ERROR;
145  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_COMMAND_BUFFER_EXP:
146  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_COMMAND_BUFFER_KHR;
147  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_COMMAND_BUFFER_SYNC_POINT_WAIT_LIST_EXP:
148  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_SYNC_POINT_WAIT_LIST_KHR;
149  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_IN_EVENT_LIST_EXEC_STATUS:
150  return PI_ERROR_EXEC_STATUS_ERROR_FOR_EVENTS_IN_WAIT_LIST;
151  case UR_RESULT_ERROR_UNKNOWN:
152  default:
153  return PI_ERROR_UNKNOWN;
154  };
155 }
156 
157 // Helper for one-liner validation
158 #define PI_ASSERT(condition, error) \
159  if (!(condition)) \
160  return error;
161 
162 // Early exits on any error
163 #define HANDLE_ERRORS(urCall) \
164  if (auto Result = urCall) \
165  return ur2piResult(Result);
166 
167 // A version of return helper that returns pi_result and not ur_result_t
168 class ReturnHelper : public UrReturnHelper {
169 public:
170  using UrReturnHelper::UrReturnHelper;
171 
172  template <class T> pi_result operator()(const T &t) {
173  return ur2piResult(UrReturnHelper::operator()(t));
174  }
175  // Array return value
176  template <class T> pi_result operator()(const T *t, size_t s) {
177  return ur2piResult(UrReturnHelper::operator()(t, s));
178  }
179  // Array return value where element type is different from T
180  template <class RetType, class T> pi_result operator()(const T *t, size_t s) {
181  return ur2piResult(UrReturnHelper::operator()<RetType>(t, s));
182  }
183 };
184 
185 // A version of return helper that supports conversion through a map
186 class ConvertHelper : public ReturnHelper {
187  using ReturnHelper::ReturnHelper;
188 
189 public:
190  // Convert the value using a conversion map
191  template <typename TypeUR, typename TypePI>
192  pi_result convert(std::function<TypePI(TypeUR)> Func) {
193  *param_value_size_ret = sizeof(TypePI);
194 
195  // There is no value to convert.
196  if (!param_value)
197  return PI_SUCCESS;
198 
199  auto pValueUR = static_cast<TypeUR *>(param_value);
200  auto pValuePI = static_cast<TypePI *>(param_value);
201 
202  // Cannot convert to a smaller storage type
203  PI_ASSERT(sizeof(TypePI) >= sizeof(TypeUR), PI_ERROR_UNKNOWN);
204 
205  *pValuePI = Func(*pValueUR);
206  return PI_SUCCESS;
207  }
208 
209  // Convert the array using a conversion map
210  template <typename TypeUR, typename TypePI>
211  pi_result convertArray(std::function<TypePI(TypeUR)> Func) {
212  // Cannot convert to a smaller element storage type
213  PI_ASSERT(sizeof(TypePI) >= sizeof(TypeUR), PI_ERROR_UNKNOWN);
214 
215  const uint32_t NumberElements =
216  *param_value_size_ret / sizeof(ur_device_partition_t);
217 
218  *param_value_size_ret *= sizeof(TypePI) / sizeof(TypeUR);
219 
220  // There is no value to convert. Adjust to a possibly bigger PI storage.
221  if (!param_value)
222  return PI_SUCCESS;
223 
224  PI_ASSERT(*param_value_size_ret % sizeof(TypePI) == 0, PI_ERROR_UNKNOWN);
225 
226  // Make a copy of the input UR array as we may possibly overwrite
227  // following elements while converting previous ones (if extending).
228  auto ValueUR = new char[*param_value_size_ret];
229  auto pValueUR = reinterpret_cast<TypeUR *>(ValueUR);
230  auto pValuePI = static_cast<TypePI *>(param_value);
231  memcpy(pValueUR, param_value, *param_value_size_ret);
232 
233  for (uint32_t I = 0; I < NumberElements; ++I) {
234  *pValuePI = Func(*pValueUR);
235  ++pValuePI;
236  ++pValueUR;
237  }
238 
239  delete[] ValueUR;
240  return PI_SUCCESS;
241  }
242 
243  // Convert the bitset using a conversion map
244  template <typename TypeUR, typename TypePI>
245  pi_result convertBitSet(std::function<TypePI(TypeUR)> Func) {
246  // There is no value to convert.
247  if (!param_value)
248  return PI_SUCCESS;
249 
250  auto pValuePI = static_cast<TypePI *>(param_value);
251  auto pValueUR = static_cast<TypeUR *>(param_value);
252 
253  // Cannot handle biteset large than size_t
254  PI_ASSERT(sizeof(TypeUR) <= sizeof(size_t), PI_ERROR_UNKNOWN);
255  size_t In = *pValueUR;
256  TypePI Out = 0;
257 
258  size_t Val;
259  while ((Val = In & -In)) { // Val is the rightmost set bit in In
260  In &= In - 1; // Reset the rightmost set bit
261 
262  // Convert the Val alone and merge it into Out
263  *pValueUR = TypeUR(Val);
264  if (auto Res = convert(Func))
265  return Res;
266  Out |= *pValuePI;
267  }
268  *pValuePI = TypePI(Out);
269  return PI_SUCCESS;
270  }
271 };
272 
273 // Handle mismatched PI and UR type return sizes for info queries
274 inline void fixupInfoValueTypes(size_t ParamValueSizeRetUR,
275  size_t *ParamValueSizeRetPI,
276  size_t ParamValueSize, void *ParamValue) {
277  if (ParamValueSizeRetUR == 1 && ParamValueSize == 4) {
278  // extend bool to pi_bool (uint32_t)
279  if (ParamValue) {
280  auto *ValIn = static_cast<bool *>(ParamValue);
281  auto *ValOut = static_cast<pi_bool *>(ParamValue);
282  *ValOut = static_cast<pi_bool>(*ValIn);
283  }
284  if (ParamValueSizeRetPI) {
285  *ParamValueSizeRetPI = sizeof(pi_bool);
286  }
287  }
288 }
289 
290 // Translate UR platform info values to PI info values
291 inline pi_result ur2piPlatformInfoValue(ur_platform_info_t ParamName,
292  size_t ParamValueSizePI,
293  size_t *ParamValueSizeUR,
294  void *ParamValue) {
295 
296  ConvertHelper Value(ParamValueSizePI, ParamValue, ParamValueSizeUR);
297 
298  switch (ParamName) {
299  case UR_PLATFORM_INFO_EXTENSIONS:
300  case UR_PLATFORM_INFO_NAME:
301  case UR_PLATFORM_INFO_PROFILE:
302  case UR_PLATFORM_INFO_VENDOR_NAME:
303  case UR_PLATFORM_INFO_VERSION:
304  // These ones do not need ur2pi translations
305  break;
306  case UR_PLATFORM_INFO_BACKEND: {
307  auto ConvertFunc = [](ur_platform_backend_t UrValue) {
308  switch (UrValue) {
309  case UR_PLATFORM_BACKEND_UNKNOWN:
310  return PI_EXT_PLATFORM_BACKEND_UNKNOWN;
311  case UR_PLATFORM_BACKEND_LEVEL_ZERO:
312  return PI_EXT_PLATFORM_BACKEND_LEVEL_ZERO;
313  case UR_PLATFORM_BACKEND_OPENCL:
314  return PI_EXT_PLATFORM_BACKEND_OPENCL;
315  case UR_PLATFORM_BACKEND_CUDA:
316  return PI_EXT_PLATFORM_BACKEND_CUDA;
317  case UR_PLATFORM_BACKEND_HIP:
318  return PI_EXT_PLATFORM_BACKEND_HIP;
319  case UR_PLATFORM_BACKEND_NATIVE_CPU:
320  return PI_EXT_PLATFORM_BACKEND_NATIVE_CPU;
321  default:
322  die("UR_PLATFORM_INFO_BACKEND: unhandled value");
323  }
324  };
325  return Value.convert<ur_platform_backend_t, pi_platform_backend>(
326  ConvertFunc);
327  }
328  default:
329  return PI_ERROR_UNKNOWN;
330  }
331 
332  if (ParamValueSizePI && ParamValueSizePI != *ParamValueSizeUR) {
333  fprintf(stderr, "UR PlatformInfoType=%d PI=%d but UR=%d\n", ParamName,
334  (int)ParamValueSizePI, (int)*ParamValueSizeUR);
335  die("ur2piPlatformInfoValue: size mismatch");
336  }
337  return PI_SUCCESS;
338 }
339 
349 inline pi_result ur2piDeviceInfoValue(ur_device_info_t ParamName,
350  size_t ParamValueSize, void *ParamValue,
351  size_t *ParamValueSizeRet) {
352 
353  /* Helper function to perform conversions in-place */
354  ConvertHelper Value(ParamValueSize, ParamValue, ParamValueSizeRet);
355 
356  pi_result Error = PI_SUCCESS;
357  if (ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_TYPE) {
358  auto ConvertFunc = [](ur_device_type_t UrValue) {
359  switch (UrValue) {
360  case UR_DEVICE_TYPE_CPU:
361  return PI_DEVICE_TYPE_CPU;
362  case UR_DEVICE_TYPE_GPU:
363  return PI_DEVICE_TYPE_GPU;
364  case UR_DEVICE_TYPE_FPGA:
365  return PI_DEVICE_TYPE_ACC;
366  default:
367  die("UR_DEVICE_INFO_TYPE: unhandled value");
368  }
369  };
370  return Value.convert<ur_device_type_t, pi_device_type>(ConvertFunc);
371  } else if (ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_QUEUE_PROPERTIES) {
372  auto ConvertFunc = [](ur_queue_flag_t UrValue) {
373  switch (UrValue) {
374  case UR_QUEUE_FLAG_OUT_OF_ORDER_EXEC_MODE_ENABLE:
375  return PI_QUEUE_FLAG_OUT_OF_ORDER_EXEC_MODE_ENABLE;
376  case UR_QUEUE_FLAG_PROFILING_ENABLE:
377  return PI_QUEUE_FLAG_PROFILING_ENABLE;
378  case UR_QUEUE_FLAG_ON_DEVICE:
379  return PI_QUEUE_FLAG_ON_DEVICE;
380  case UR_QUEUE_FLAG_ON_DEVICE_DEFAULT:
381  return PI_QUEUE_FLAG_ON_DEVICE_DEFAULT;
382  case UR_QUEUE_FLAG_SYNC_WITH_DEFAULT_STREAM:
383  return static_cast<uint64_t>(__SYCL_PI_CUDA_SYNC_WITH_DEFAULT);
384  case UR_QUEUE_FLAG_USE_DEFAULT_STREAM:
385  return static_cast<uint64_t>(__SYCL_PI_CUDA_USE_DEFAULT_STREAM);
386  default:
387  die("UR_DEVICE_INFO_QUEUE_PROPERTIES: unhandled value");
388  }
389  };
390  return Value.convertBitSet<ur_queue_flag_t, pi_queue_properties>(
391  ConvertFunc);
392  } else if (ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_EXECUTION_CAPABILITIES) {
393  auto ConvertFunc = [](ur_device_exec_capability_flag_t UrValue) {
394  switch (UrValue) {
395  case UR_DEVICE_EXEC_CAPABILITY_FLAG_KERNEL:
396  return PI_DEVICE_EXEC_CAPABILITIES_KERNEL;
397  case UR_DEVICE_EXEC_CAPABILITY_FLAG_NATIVE_KERNEL:
398  return PI_DEVICE_EXEC_CAPABILITIES_NATIVE_KERNEL;
399  default:
400  die("UR_DEVICE_INFO_EXECUTION_CAPABILITIES: unhandled value");
401  }
402  };
403  return Value
404  .convertBitSet<ur_device_exec_capability_flag_t, pi_queue_properties>(
405  ConvertFunc);
406  } else if (ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_PARTITION_AFFINITY_DOMAIN) {
407  auto ConvertFunc = [](ur_device_affinity_domain_flag_t UrValue) {
408  switch (UrValue) {
409  case UR_DEVICE_AFFINITY_DOMAIN_FLAG_NUMA:
410  return PI_DEVICE_AFFINITY_DOMAIN_NUMA;
411  case UR_DEVICE_AFFINITY_DOMAIN_FLAG_NEXT_PARTITIONABLE:
412  return PI_DEVICE_AFFINITY_DOMAIN_NEXT_PARTITIONABLE;
413  default:
414  die("UR_DEVICE_INFO_PARTITION_AFFINITY_DOMAIN: unhandled value");
415  }
416  };
417  return Value.convertBitSet<ur_device_affinity_domain_flag_t,
418  pi_device_affinity_domain>(ConvertFunc);
419  } else if (ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_PARTITION_TYPE) {
420 
421  auto ConvertFunc = [](ur_device_partition_t UrValue) {
422  switch (static_cast<uint32_t>(UrValue)) {
423  case UR_DEVICE_PARTITION_EQUALLY:
424  return PI_DEVICE_PARTITION_EQUALLY;
425  case UR_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_COUNTS:
426  return PI_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_COUNTS;
427  case UR_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_AFFINITY_DOMAIN:
428  return PI_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_AFFINITY_DOMAIN;
429  case UR_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_CSLICE:
430  return PI_EXT_INTEL_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_CSLICE;
431  default:
432  die("UR_DEVICE_INFO_PARTITION_TYPE: unhandled value");
433  }
434  };
435 
436  /*
437  * This property returns the argument specified in piCreateSubDevices.
438  * Each partition name is immediately followed by a value. The list is
439  * terminated with 0. In the case where the properties argument to
440  * piCreateSubDevices is [PI_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_AFFINITY_DOMAIN,
441  * PI_DEVICE_AFFINITY_DOMAIN_NEXT_PARTITIONABLE], the affinity domain used
442  * to perform the partition will be returned. */
443 
444  PI_ASSERT(sizeof(pi_device_partition_property) ==
445  sizeof(ur_device_partition_property_t),
446  PI_ERROR_UNKNOWN);
447 
448  const uint32_t UrNumberElements =
449  *ParamValueSizeRet / sizeof(ur_device_partition_property_t);
450 
451  if (ParamValue) {
452  auto ParamValueCopy =
453  std::make_unique<ur_device_partition_property_t[]>(UrNumberElements);
454  std::memcpy(ParamValueCopy.get(), ParamValue,
455  UrNumberElements * sizeof(ur_device_partition_property_t));
456  pi_device_partition_property *pValuePI =
457  reinterpret_cast<pi_device_partition_property *>(ParamValue);
458  ur_device_partition_property_t *pValueUR =
459  reinterpret_cast<ur_device_partition_property_t *>(
460  ParamValueCopy.get());
461  const ur_device_partition_t Type = pValueUR->type;
462  *pValuePI = ConvertFunc(Type);
463  ++pValuePI;
464 
465  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < UrNumberElements; ++i) {
466  switch (pValueUR->type) {
467  case UR_DEVICE_PARTITION_EQUALLY: {
468  *pValuePI = pValueUR->value.equally;
469  break;
470  }
471  case UR_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_COUNTS: {
472  *pValuePI = pValueUR->value.count;
473  break;
474  }
475  case UR_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_AFFINITY_DOMAIN: {
476  *pValuePI = pValueUR->value.affinity_domain;
477  break;
478  }
479  case UR_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_CSLICE: {
480  *pValuePI = 0;
481  break;
482  }
483  default:
484  die("UR_DEVICE_INFO_PARTITION_TYPE query returned unsupported type");
485  }
486  ++pValuePI;
487  ++pValueUR;
488  }
489  *pValuePI = 0;
490  }
491 
492  if (ParamValueSizeRet && *ParamValueSizeRet != 0) {
493  /* Add 2 extra elements to the return value (one for the type at the
494  * beginning and another to terminate the array with a 0 */
495  *ParamValueSizeRet =
496  (UrNumberElements + 2) * sizeof(pi_device_partition_property);
497  }
498  }
499 
500  else if (ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_SUPPORTED_PARTITIONS) {
501  auto ConvertFunc = [](ur_device_partition_t UrValue) {
502  switch (static_cast<uint32_t>(UrValue)) {
503  case UR_DEVICE_PARTITION_EQUALLY:
504  return PI_DEVICE_PARTITION_EQUALLY;
505  case UR_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_COUNTS:
506  return PI_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_COUNTS;
507  case UR_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_AFFINITY_DOMAIN:
508  return PI_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_AFFINITY_DOMAIN;
509  case UR_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_CSLICE:
510  return PI_EXT_INTEL_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_CSLICE;
511  default:
512  die("UR_DEVICE_INFO_SUPPORTED_PARTITIONS: unhandled value");
513  }
514  };
515 
516  Value.convertArray<ur_device_partition_t, pi_device_partition_property>(
517  ConvertFunc);
518 
519  if (ParamValue) {
520  const uint32_t NumberElements =
521  *ParamValueSizeRet / sizeof(pi_device_partition_property);
522  reinterpret_cast<pi_device_partition_property *>(
523  ParamValue)[NumberElements] = 0;
524  }
525 
526  if (ParamValueSizeRet && *ParamValueSizeRet != 0) {
527  *ParamValueSizeRet += sizeof(pi_device_partition_property);
528  }
529 
530  } else if (ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_LOCAL_MEM_TYPE) {
531  auto ConvertFunc = [](ur_device_local_mem_type_t UrValue) {
532  switch (UrValue) {
533  case UR_DEVICE_LOCAL_MEM_TYPE_LOCAL:
534  return PI_DEVICE_LOCAL_MEM_TYPE_LOCAL;
535  case UR_DEVICE_LOCAL_MEM_TYPE_GLOBAL:
536  return PI_DEVICE_LOCAL_MEM_TYPE_GLOBAL;
537  default:
538  die("UR_DEVICE_INFO_LOCAL_MEM_TYPE: unhandled value");
539  }
540  };
541  return Value.convert<ur_device_local_mem_type_t, pi_device_local_mem_type>(
542  ConvertFunc);
543  } else if (ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_ATOMIC_MEMORY_ORDER_CAPABILITIES ||
544  ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_ATOMIC_FENCE_ORDER_CAPABILITIES) {
545  auto ConvertFunc = [](ur_memory_order_capability_flag_t UrValue) {
546  switch (UrValue) {
547  case UR_MEMORY_ORDER_CAPABILITY_FLAG_RELAXED:
548  return PI_MEMORY_ORDER_RELAXED;
549  case UR_MEMORY_ORDER_CAPABILITY_FLAG_ACQUIRE:
550  return PI_MEMORY_ORDER_ACQUIRE;
551  case UR_MEMORY_ORDER_CAPABILITY_FLAG_RELEASE:
552  return PI_MEMORY_ORDER_RELEASE;
553  case UR_MEMORY_ORDER_CAPABILITY_FLAG_ACQ_REL:
554  return PI_MEMORY_ORDER_ACQ_REL;
555  case UR_MEMORY_ORDER_CAPABILITY_FLAG_SEQ_CST:
556  return PI_MEMORY_ORDER_SEQ_CST;
557  default:
558  die("UR_DEVICE_INFO_ATOMIC_MEMORY_ORDER_CAPABILITIES: unhandled "
559  "value");
560  }
561  };
562  return Value.convertBitSet<ur_memory_order_capability_flag_t,
563  pi_memory_order_capabilities>(ConvertFunc);
564  } else if (ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_ATOMIC_MEMORY_SCOPE_CAPABILITIES ||
565  ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_ATOMIC_FENCE_SCOPE_CAPABILITIES) {
566  auto ConvertFunc = [](ur_memory_scope_capability_flag_t UrValue) {
567  switch (UrValue) {
568  case UR_MEMORY_SCOPE_CAPABILITY_FLAG_WORK_ITEM:
569  return PI_MEMORY_SCOPE_WORK_ITEM;
570  case UR_MEMORY_SCOPE_CAPABILITY_FLAG_SUB_GROUP:
571  return PI_MEMORY_SCOPE_SUB_GROUP;
572  case UR_MEMORY_SCOPE_CAPABILITY_FLAG_WORK_GROUP:
573  return PI_MEMORY_SCOPE_WORK_GROUP;
574  case UR_MEMORY_SCOPE_CAPABILITY_FLAG_DEVICE:
575  return PI_MEMORY_SCOPE_DEVICE;
576  case UR_MEMORY_SCOPE_CAPABILITY_FLAG_SYSTEM:
577  return PI_MEMORY_SCOPE_SYSTEM;
578  default:
579  die("UR_DEVICE_INFO_ATOMIC_MEMORY_SCOPE_CAPABILITIES: unhandled "
580  "value");
581  }
582  };
583  return Value.convertBitSet<ur_memory_scope_capability_flag_t,
584  pi_memory_scope_capabilities>(ConvertFunc);
585  } else if (*ParamValueSizeRet == 1 && ParamValueSize == 4) {
586  /* PI type: pi_bool
587  * UR type: ur_bool_t
588  * Need to convert from pi_bool (4 bytes) to ur_bool_t (1 byte)
589  */
590  fixupInfoValueTypes(*ParamValueSizeRet, ParamValueSizeRet, ParamValueSize,
591  ParamValue);
592  } else if (ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_QUEUE_PROPERTIES ||
593  ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_QUEUE_ON_DEVICE_PROPERTIES ||
594  ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_QUEUE_ON_HOST_PROPERTIES ||
595  ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_EXECUTION_CAPABILITIES ||
596  ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_PARTITION_AFFINITY_DOMAIN ||
597  ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_USM_HOST_SUPPORT ||
598  ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_USM_DEVICE_SUPPORT ||
599  ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_USM_SINGLE_SHARED_SUPPORT ||
600  ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_USM_CROSS_SHARED_SUPPORT ||
601  ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_USM_SYSTEM_SHARED_SUPPORT) {
602  /* PI type: pi_bitfield
603  * UR type: ur_flags_t (uint32_t)
604  * No need to convert since types are compatible
605  */
606  *ParamValueSizeRet = sizeof(pi_bitfield);
607  } else if (ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_SINGLE_FP_CONFIG ||
608  ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_HALF_FP_CONFIG ||
609  ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_DOUBLE_FP_CONFIG) {
610  /* CL type: pi_device_fp_config
611  * UR type: ur_device_fp_capability_flags_t
612  * No need to convert since types are compatible
613  */
614  *ParamValueSizeRet = sizeof(pi_device_fp_config);
615  } else if (ParamName == UR_DEVICE_INFO_COMPONENT_DEVICES) {
616  if (ParamValueSizeRet && *ParamValueSizeRet != 0) {
617  const uint32_t UrNumberElements =
618  *ParamValueSizeRet / sizeof(ur_device_handle_t);
619  *ParamValueSizeRet = UrNumberElements * sizeof(pi_device);
620  }
621  } else {
622 
623  // TODO: what else needs a UR-PI translation?
624  }
625 
626  if (ParamValueSize && ParamValueSizeRet &&
627  ParamValueSize != *ParamValueSizeRet) {
628  fprintf(stderr, "UR DeviceInfoType=%d PI=%d but UR=%d\n", ParamName,
629  (int)ParamValueSize, (int)*ParamValueSizeRet);
630  die("ur2piDeviceInfoValue: size mismatch");
631  }
632  return Error;
633 }
634 
635 inline pi_result ur2piSamplerInfoValue(ur_sampler_info_t ParamName,
636  size_t ParamValueSizePI,
637  size_t *ParamValueSizeUR,
638  void *ParamValue) {
639 
640  ConvertHelper Value(ParamValueSizePI, ParamValue, ParamValueSizeUR);
641  switch (ParamName) {
642  case UR_SAMPLER_INFO_ADDRESSING_MODE: {
643  auto ConvertFunc = [](ur_sampler_addressing_mode_t UrValue) {
644  switch (UrValue) {
645  case UR_SAMPLER_ADDRESSING_MODE_CLAMP:
646  return PI_SAMPLER_ADDRESSING_MODE_CLAMP;
647  case UR_SAMPLER_ADDRESSING_MODE_CLAMP_TO_EDGE:
648  return PI_SAMPLER_ADDRESSING_MODE_CLAMP_TO_EDGE;
649  case UR_SAMPLER_ADDRESSING_MODE_MIRRORED_REPEAT:
650  return PI_SAMPLER_ADDRESSING_MODE_MIRRORED_REPEAT;
651  case UR_SAMPLER_ADDRESSING_MODE_NONE:
652  return PI_SAMPLER_ADDRESSING_MODE_NONE;
653  case UR_SAMPLER_ADDRESSING_MODE_REPEAT:
654  return PI_SAMPLER_ADDRESSING_MODE_REPEAT;
655 
656  default:
657  die("UR_SAMPLER_ADDRESSING_MODE_TYPE: unhandled value");
658  }
659  };
660  return Value
661  .convert<ur_sampler_addressing_mode_t, pi_sampler_addressing_mode>(
662  ConvertFunc);
663  }
664  case UR_SAMPLER_INFO_FILTER_MODE: {
665  auto ConvertFunc = [](ur_sampler_filter_mode_t UrValue) {
666  switch (UrValue) {
667  case UR_SAMPLER_FILTER_MODE_LINEAR:
668  return PI_SAMPLER_FILTER_MODE_LINEAR;
669  case UR_SAMPLER_FILTER_MODE_NEAREST:
670  return PI_SAMPLER_FILTER_MODE_NEAREST;
671  default:
672  die("UR_SAMPLER_FILTER_MODE: unhandled value");
673  }
674  };
675  return Value.convert<ur_sampler_filter_mode_t, pi_sampler_filter_mode>(
676  ConvertFunc);
677  }
678  default:
679  return PI_SUCCESS;
680  }
681 }

683 // Translate UR device info values to PI info values
684 inline pi_result ur2piUSMAllocInfoValue(ur_usm_alloc_info_t ParamName,
685  size_t ParamValueSizePI,
686  size_t *ParamValueSizeUR,
687  void *ParamValue) {
688  ConvertHelper Value(ParamValueSizePI, ParamValue, ParamValueSizeUR);
689 
690  if (ParamName == UR_USM_ALLOC_INFO_TYPE) {
691  auto ConvertFunc = [](ur_usm_type_t UrValue) {
692  switch (UrValue) {
693  case UR_USM_TYPE_UNKNOWN:
694  return PI_MEM_TYPE_UNKNOWN;
695  case UR_USM_TYPE_HOST:
696  return PI_MEM_TYPE_HOST;
697  case UR_USM_TYPE_DEVICE:
698  return PI_MEM_TYPE_DEVICE;
699  case UR_USM_TYPE_SHARED:
700  return PI_MEM_TYPE_SHARED;
701  default:
702  die("UR_USM_ALLOC_INFO_TYPE: unhandled value");
703  }
704  };
705  return Value.convert<ur_usm_type_t, pi_usm_type>(ConvertFunc);
706  }
707 
708  return PI_SUCCESS;
709 }

711 // Translate UR program build info values to PI info values
712 inline pi_result ur2piProgramBuildInfoValue(ur_program_build_info_t ParamName,
713  size_t ParamValueSizePI,
714  size_t *ParamValueSizeUR,
715  void *ParamValue) {
716  ConvertHelper Value(ParamValueSizePI, ParamValue, ParamValueSizeUR);
717 
718  if (ParamName == UR_PROGRAM_BUILD_INFO_BINARY_TYPE) {
719  auto ConvertFunc = [](ur_program_binary_type_t UrValue) {
720  switch (UrValue) {
721  case UR_PROGRAM_BINARY_TYPE_NONE:
722  return PI_PROGRAM_BINARY_TYPE_NONE;
723  case UR_PROGRAM_BINARY_TYPE_COMPILED_OBJECT:
724  return PI_PROGRAM_BINARY_TYPE_COMPILED_OBJECT;
725  case UR_PROGRAM_BINARY_TYPE_LIBRARY:
726  return PI_PROGRAM_BINARY_TYPE_LIBRARY;
727  case UR_PROGRAM_BINARY_TYPE_EXECUTABLE:
728  return PI_PROGRAM_BINARY_TYPE_EXECUTABLE;
729  default:
730  die("ur_program_binary_type_t: unhandled value");
731  }
732  };
733  return Value.convert<ur_program_binary_type_t, pi_program_binary_type>(
734  ConvertFunc);
735  }
736 
737  if (ParamName == UR_PROGRAM_BUILD_INFO_STATUS) {
738  auto ConvertFunc = [](ur_program_build_status_t UrValue) {
739  switch (UrValue) {
740  case UR_PROGRAM_BUILD_STATUS_NONE:
741  return PI_PROGRAM_BUILD_STATUS_NONE;
742  case UR_PROGRAM_BUILD_STATUS_ERROR:
743  return PI_PROGRAM_BUILD_STATUS_ERROR;
744  case UR_PROGRAM_BUILD_STATUS_SUCCESS:
745  return PI_PROGRAM_BUILD_STATUS_SUCCESS;
746  case UR_PROGRAM_BUILD_STATUS_IN_PROGRESS:
747  return PI_PROGRAM_BUILD_STATUS_IN_PROGRESS;
748  default:
749  die("ur_program_build_status_t: unhandled value");
750  }
751  };
752  return Value.convert<ur_program_build_status_t, pi_program_build_status>(
753  ConvertFunc);
754  }
755 
756  return PI_SUCCESS;
757 }

759 inline ur_result_t
760 mapPIMetadataToUR(const pi_device_binary_property *pi_metadata,
761  ur_program_metadata_t *ur_metadata) {
762  ur_metadata->pName = (*pi_metadata)->Name;
763  ur_metadata->size = (*pi_metadata)->ValSize;
764  switch ((*pi_metadata)->Type) {
765  case PI_PROPERTY_TYPE_UINT32:
766  ur_metadata->type = UR_PROGRAM_METADATA_TYPE_UINT32;
767  ur_metadata->value.data32 = (*pi_metadata)->ValSize;
768  return UR_RESULT_SUCCESS;
769  case PI_PROPERTY_TYPE_BYTE_ARRAY:
770  ur_metadata->type = UR_PROGRAM_METADATA_TYPE_BYTE_ARRAY;
771  ur_metadata->value.pData = (*pi_metadata)->ValAddr;
772  return UR_RESULT_SUCCESS;
773  case PI_PROPERTY_TYPE_STRING:
774  ur_metadata->type = UR_PROGRAM_METADATA_TYPE_STRING;
775  ur_metadata->value.pString =
776  reinterpret_cast<char *>((*pi_metadata)->ValAddr);
777  return UR_RESULT_SUCCESS;
778  default:
779  return UR_RESULT_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE;
780  }
781 }

785 inline pi_result piTearDown(void *PluginParameter) {
786  bool *pluginTeardown = static_cast<bool *>(PluginParameter);
787  *pluginTeardown = true;
788  // Fetch the single known adapter (the one which is statically linked) so we
789  // can release it. Fetching it for a second time (after piPlatformsGet)
790  // increases the reference count, so we need to release it twice.
791  // pi_unified_runtime has its own implementation of piTearDown.
792  static std::once_flag AdapterReleaseFlag;
793  ur_adapter_handle_t Adapter;
794  ur_result_t Ret = UR_RESULT_SUCCESS;
795  std::call_once(AdapterReleaseFlag, [&]() {
796  Ret = urAdapterGet(1, &Adapter, nullptr);
797  if (Ret == UR_RESULT_SUCCESS) {
798  Ret = urAdapterRelease(Adapter);
799  Ret = urAdapterRelease(Adapter);
800  }
801  });
802  HANDLE_ERRORS(Ret);
803 
804  return PI_SUCCESS;
805 }
806 
807 inline pi_result PiGetAdapter(ur_adapter_handle_t &adapter) {
808  // We're not going through the UR loader so we're guaranteed to have exactly
809  // one adapter (whichever is statically linked). The PI plugin for UR has its
810  // own implementation of piPlatformsGet.
811  static ur_adapter_handle_t Adapter;
812  static std::once_flag AdapterGetFlag;
813  ur_result_t Ret = UR_RESULT_SUCCESS;
814  std::call_once(AdapterGetFlag,
815  [&Ret]() { Ret = urAdapterGet(1, &Adapter, nullptr); });
816  HANDLE_ERRORS(Ret);
817 
818  adapter = Adapter;
819 
820  return PI_SUCCESS;
821 }
822 
824 // Platform
825 inline pi_result piPlatformsGet(pi_uint32 NumEntries, pi_platform *Platforms,
826  pi_uint32 *NumPlatforms) {
827  ur_adapter_handle_t adapter = nullptr;
828  if (auto res = PiGetAdapter(adapter); res != PI_SUCCESS) {
829  return res;
830  }
831 
832  auto phPlatforms = reinterpret_cast<ur_platform_handle_t *>(Platforms);
833  HANDLE_ERRORS(
834  urPlatformGet(&adapter, 1, NumEntries, phPlatforms, NumPlatforms));
835  return PI_SUCCESS;
836 }

838 inline pi_result piextPlatformGetNativeHandle(pi_platform Platform,
839  pi_native_handle *NativeHandle) {
840

842  PI_ASSERT(NativeHandle, PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE);
843 
844  auto UrPlatform = reinterpret_cast<ur_platform_handle_t>(Platform);
845 
846  ur_native_handle_t UrNativeHandle{};
847  HANDLE_ERRORS(urPlatformGetNativeHandle(UrPlatform, &UrNativeHandle));

850

854 inline pi_result
855 piextPlatformCreateWithNativeHandle(pi_native_handle NativeHandle,
856  pi_platform *Platform) {
857 
858  PI_ASSERT(Platform, PI_ERROR_INVALID_PLATFORM);
859  PI_ASSERT(NativeHandle, PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE);
860 
861  ur_adapter_handle_t adapter = nullptr;
862  if (auto res = PiGetAdapter(adapter); res != PI_SUCCESS) {
863  return res;
864  }
865  (void)adapter;
866 
867  ur_platform_handle_t UrPlatform{};
868  ur_native_handle_t UrNativeHandle =
869  reinterpret_cast<ur_native_handle_t>(NativeHandle);
870  ur_platform_native_properties_t UrProperties{};
871  urPlatformCreateWithNativeHandle(UrNativeHandle, &UrProperties, &UrPlatform);
872 
873  *Platform = reinterpret_cast<pi_platform>(UrPlatform);
874 
875  return PI_SUCCESS;
876 }

878 inline pi_result piPlatformGetInfo(pi_platform Platform,
879  pi_platform_info ParamName,
880  size_t ParamValueSize, void *ParamValue,
881  size_t *ParamValueSizeRet) {
882 
883  PI_ASSERT(Platform, PI_ERROR_INVALID_PLATFORM);
884 
885  ur_platform_info_t UrParamName = {};
886  switch (ParamName) {
887  case PI_PLATFORM_INFO_EXTENSIONS: {
888  UrParamName = UR_PLATFORM_INFO_EXTENSIONS;
889  break;
890  }
891  case PI_PLATFORM_INFO_NAME: {
892  UrParamName = UR_PLATFORM_INFO_NAME;
893  break;
894  }
895  case PI_PLATFORM_INFO_PROFILE: {
896  UrParamName = UR_PLATFORM_INFO_PROFILE;
897  break;
898  }
899  case PI_PLATFORM_INFO_VENDOR: {
900  UrParamName = UR_PLATFORM_INFO_VENDOR_NAME;
901  break;
902  }
903  case PI_PLATFORM_INFO_VERSION: {
904  UrParamName = UR_PLATFORM_INFO_VERSION;
905  break;
906  }
907  case PI_EXT_PLATFORM_INFO_BACKEND: {
908  UrParamName = UR_PLATFORM_INFO_BACKEND;
909  break;
910  }
911  default:
912  die("urGetContextInfo: unsuppported ParamName.");
913  }
914 
915  size_t UrParamValueSizeRet;
916  auto UrPlatform = reinterpret_cast<ur_platform_handle_t>(Platform);
917  HANDLE_ERRORS(urPlatformGetInfo(UrPlatform, UrParamName, ParamValueSize,
918  ParamValue, &UrParamValueSizeRet));
919 
920  if (ParamValueSizeRet) {
921  *ParamValueSizeRet = UrParamValueSizeRet;
922  }
923  ur2piPlatformInfoValue(UrParamName, ParamValueSize, &ParamValueSize,
924  ParamValue);
925  fixupInfoValueTypes(UrParamValueSizeRet, ParamValueSizeRet, ParamValueSize,
926  ParamValue);
927 
928  return PI_SUCCESS;
929 }

954 inline pi_result piDevicesGet(pi_platform Platform, pi_device_type DeviceType,
955  pi_uint32 NumEntries, pi_device *Devices,
956  pi_uint32 *NumDevices) {
957  ur_device_type_t Type;
958  switch (DeviceType) {
959  case PI_DEVICE_TYPE_ALL:
960  Type = UR_DEVICE_TYPE_ALL;
961  break;
962  case PI_DEVICE_TYPE_GPU:
963  Type = UR_DEVICE_TYPE_GPU;
964  break;
965  case PI_DEVICE_TYPE_CPU:
966  Type = UR_DEVICE_TYPE_CPU;
967  break;
968  case PI_DEVICE_TYPE_ACC:
969  Type = UR_DEVICE_TYPE_FPGA;
970  break;
971  default:
972  return PI_ERROR_UNKNOWN;
973  }
974 
975  PI_ASSERT(Platform, PI_ERROR_INVALID_PLATFORM);
976 
977  auto UrPlatform = reinterpret_cast<ur_platform_handle_t>(Platform);
978  auto UrDevices = reinterpret_cast<ur_device_handle_t *>(Devices);
979  HANDLE_ERRORS(
980  urDeviceGet(UrPlatform, Type, NumEntries, UrDevices, NumDevices));
981 
982  return PI_SUCCESS;
983 }

1000 inline pi_result piPluginGetLastError(char **Message) {
1001  // We're not going through the UR loader so we're guaranteed to have exactly
1002  // one adapter (whichever is statically linked). The PI plugin for UR has its
1003  // own implementation of piPluginGetLastError. Materialize the adapter
1004  // reference for the urAdapterGetLastError call, then release it.
1005  ur_adapter_handle_t Adapter;
1006  urAdapterGet(1, &Adapter, nullptr);
1007  // FIXME: ErrorCode should store a native error, but these are not being used
1008  // in CUDA adapter at the moment
1009  int32_t ErrorCode;
1010  ur_result_t Res = urAdapterGetLastError(
1011  Adapter, const_cast<const char **>(Message), &ErrorCode);
1012  urAdapterRelease(Adapter);
1013 
1014  return ur2piResult(Res);
1015 }

1017 inline pi_result piDeviceGetInfo(pi_device Device, pi_device_info ParamName,
1018  size_t ParamValueSize, void *ParamValue,
1019  size_t *ParamValueSizeRet) {
1020  ur_device_info_t InfoType;
1021  switch (ParamName) {
1022 #define PI_TO_UR_MAP_DEVICE_INFO(FROM, TO) \
1023  case FROM: { \
1024  InfoType = TO; \
1025  break; \
1026  }
1027  PI_TO_UR_MAP_DEVICE_INFO(PI_DEVICE_INFO_TYPE, UR_DEVICE_INFO_TYPE)
1028  PI_TO_UR_MAP_DEVICE_INFO(PI_DEVICE_INFO_PARENT_DEVICE,
1029  UR_DEVICE_INFO_PARENT_DEVICE)
1030  PI_TO_UR_MAP_DEVICE_INFO(PI_DEVICE_INFO_PLATFORM, UR_DEVICE_INFO_PLATFORM)
1031  PI_TO_UR_MAP_DEVICE_INFO(PI_DEVICE_INFO_VENDOR_ID, UR_DEVICE_INFO_VENDOR_ID)
1032  PI_TO_UR_MAP_DEVICE_INFO(PI_DEVICE_INFO_UUID, UR_DEVICE_INFO_UUID)
1033  PI_TO_UR_MAP_DEVICE_INFO(PI_DEVICE_INFO_ATOMIC_64, UR_DEVICE_INFO_ATOMIC_64)
1034  PI_TO_UR_MAP_DEVICE_INFO(PI_DEVICE_INFO_EXTENSIONS,
1035  UR_DEVICE_INFO_EXTENSIONS)
1036  PI_TO_UR_MAP_DEVICE_INFO(PI_DEVICE_INFO_NAME, UR_DEVICE_INFO_NAME)
1037  PI_TO_UR_MAP_DEVICE_INFO(PI_DEVICE_INFO_COMPILER_AVAILABLE,
1038  UR_DEVICE_INFO_COMPILER_AVAILABLE)
1039  PI_TO_UR_MAP_DEVICE_INFO(PI_DEVICE_INFO_LINKER_AVAILABLE,
1040  UR_DEVICE_INFO_LINKER_AVAILABLE)
1041  PI_TO_UR_MAP_DEVICE_INFO(PI_DEVICE_INFO_MAX_COMPUTE_UNITS,
1042  UR_DEVICE_INFO_MAX_COMPUTE_UNITS)
1043  PI_TO_UR_MAP_DEVICE_INFO(PI_DEVICE_INFO_MAX_WORK_ITEM_DIMENSIONS,
1044  UR_DEVICE_INFO_MAX_WORK_ITEM_DIMENSIONS)
1045  PI_TO_UR_MAP_DEVICE_INFO(PI_DEVICE_INFO_MAX_WORK_GROUP_SIZE,
1046  UR_DEVICE_INFO_MAX_WORK_GROUP_SIZE)

1048  UR_DEVICE_INFO_MAX_WORK_ITEM_SIZES)

1058  UR_DEVICE_INFO_LOCAL_MEM_SIZE)

1062  UR_DEVICE_INFO_HOST_UNIFIED_MEMORY)
1063  PI_TO_UR_MAP_DEVICE_INFO(PI_DEVICE_INFO_AVAILABLE, UR_DEVICE_INFO_AVAILABLE)
1064  PI_TO_UR_MAP_DEVICE_INFO(PI_DEVICE_INFO_VENDOR, UR_DEVICE_INFO_VENDOR)

1068  PI_TO_UR_MAP_DEVICE_INFO(PI_DEVICE_INFO_PARTITION_MAX_SUB_DEVICES,

1314  default:
1315  return PI_ERROR_UNKNOWN;
1316  };
1317 
1318  PI_ASSERT(Device, PI_ERROR_INVALID_DEVICE);
1319 
1320  size_t ParamValueSizeRetUR;
1321  auto DeviceUR = reinterpret_cast<ur_device_handle_t>(Device);
1322 
1323  HANDLE_ERRORS(urDeviceGetInfo(DeviceUR, InfoType, ParamValueSize, ParamValue,
1324  &ParamValueSizeRetUR));
1325 
1326  ur2piDeviceInfoValue(InfoType, ParamValueSize, ParamValue,
1327  &ParamValueSizeRetUR);
1328 
1329  if (ParamValueSizeRet) {
1330  *ParamValueSizeRet = ParamValueSizeRetUR;
1331  }
1332 
1333  return PI_SUCCESS;
1334 }

1336 inline pi_result piextDeviceGetNativeHandle(pi_device Device,
1337  pi_native_handle *NativeHandle) {
1338  PI_ASSERT(Device, PI_ERROR_INVALID_DEVICE);
1339  PI_ASSERT(NativeHandle, PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE);
1340 
1341  auto UrDevice = reinterpret_cast<ur_device_handle_t>(Device);
1342 
1343  ur_native_handle_t UrNativeHandle{};
1344  HANDLE_ERRORS(urDeviceGetNativeHandle(UrDevice, &UrNativeHandle));
1345  *NativeHandle = reinterpret_cast<pi_native_handle>(UrNativeHandle);
1346  return PI_SUCCESS;
1347 }
1348 
1349 inline pi_result
1350 piextDeviceCreateWithNativeHandle(pi_native_handle NativeHandle,
1351  pi_platform Platform, pi_device *Device) {
1352 
1353  PI_ASSERT(Device, PI_ERROR_INVALID_DEVICE);
1354  PI_ASSERT(NativeHandle, PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE);
1355 
1356  ur_adapter_handle_t adapter = nullptr;
1357  if (auto res = PiGetAdapter(adapter); res != PI_SUCCESS) {
1358  return res;
1359  }
1360  (void)adapter;
1361 
1362  ur_native_handle_t UrNativeDevice =
1363  reinterpret_cast<ur_native_handle_t>(NativeHandle);
1364  ur_platform_handle_t UrPlatform =
1365  reinterpret_cast<ur_platform_handle_t>(Platform);
1366  auto UrDevice = reinterpret_cast<ur_device_handle_t *>(Device);
1367  ur_device_native_properties_t UrProperties{};
1368  HANDLE_ERRORS(urDeviceCreateWithNativeHandle(UrNativeDevice, UrPlatform,
1369  &UrProperties, UrDevice));
1370 
1371  return PI_SUCCESS;
1372 }
1373 
1374 inline pi_result piDevicePartition(
1375  pi_device Device, const pi_device_partition_property *Properties,
1376  pi_uint32 NumEntries, pi_device *SubDevices, pi_uint32 *NumSubDevices) {
1377 
1378  PI_ASSERT(Device, PI_ERROR_INVALID_DEVICE);
1379 
1380  if (!Properties || !Properties[0]) {
1381  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE;
1382  }
1383 
1384  ur_device_partition_t UrType;
1385  switch (Properties[0]) {
1386  case PI_DEVICE_PARTITION_EQUALLY:
1387  UrType = UR_DEVICE_PARTITION_EQUALLY;
1388  break;
1389  case PI_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_COUNTS:
1390  UrType = UR_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_COUNTS;
1391  break;
1392  case PI_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_AFFINITY_DOMAIN:
1393  UrType = UR_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_AFFINITY_DOMAIN;
1394  break;
1395  case PI_EXT_INTEL_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_CSLICE:
1396  UrType = UR_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_CSLICE;
1397  break;
1398  default:
1399  return PI_ERROR_UNKNOWN;
1400  }
1401 
1402  std::vector<ur_device_partition_property_t> UrProperties{};
1403 
1404  // UR_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_CSLICE doesn't have a value, so
1405  // handle it outside the while loop below.
1406  if (UrType == UR_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_CSLICE) {
1407  ur_device_partition_property_t UrProperty{};
1408  UrProperty.type = UrType;
1409  UrProperties.push_back(UrProperty);
1410  }
1411  while (*(++Properties)) {
1412  ur_device_partition_property_t UrProperty;
1413  UrProperty.type = UrType;
1414  switch (UrType) {
1415  case UR_DEVICE_PARTITION_EQUALLY: {
1416  UrProperty.value.equally = *Properties;
1417  break;
1418  }
1419  case UR_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_COUNTS: {
1420  UrProperty.value.count = *Properties;
1421  break;
1422  }
1423  case UR_DEVICE_PARTITION_BY_AFFINITY_DOMAIN: {
1424  /* No need to convert affinity domain enums from pi to ur because they
1425  * are equivalent */
1426  UrProperty.value.affinity_domain = *Properties;
1427  break;
1428  }
1429  default: {
1430  die("Invalid properties for call to piDevicePartition");
1431  }
1432  }
1433  UrProperties.push_back(UrProperty);
1434  }
1435 
1436  const ur_device_partition_properties_t UrPropertiesStruct{
1437  UR_STRUCTURE_TYPE_DEVICE_PARTITION_PROPERTIES,
1438  nullptr,
1439  UrProperties.data(),
1440  UrProperties.size(),
1441  };
1442 
1443  auto UrDevice = reinterpret_cast<ur_device_handle_t>(Device);
1444  auto UrSubDevices = reinterpret_cast<ur_device_handle_t *>(SubDevices);
1445  HANDLE_ERRORS(urDevicePartition(UrDevice, &UrPropertiesStruct, NumEntries,
1446  UrSubDevices, NumSubDevices));
1447  return PI_SUCCESS;
1448 }
1449 
1450 inline pi_result piGetDeviceAndHostTimer(pi_device Device, uint64_t *DeviceTime,
1451  uint64_t *HostTime) {
1452  auto UrDevice = reinterpret_cast<ur_device_handle_t>(Device);
1453  HANDLE_ERRORS(urDeviceGetGlobalTimestamps(UrDevice, DeviceTime, HostTime));
1454  return PI_SUCCESS;
1455 }
1456 
1457 inline pi_result
1458 piextDeviceSelectBinary(pi_device Device, // TODO: does this need to be context?
1459  pi_device_binary *Binaries, pi_uint32 NumBinaries,
1460  pi_uint32 *SelectedBinaryInd) {
1461 
1462  auto UrDevice = reinterpret_cast<ur_device_handle_t>(Device);
1463  std::vector<ur_device_binary_t> UrBinaries(NumBinaries);
1464 
1465  for (uint32_t BinaryCount = 0; BinaryCount < NumBinaries; BinaryCount++) {
1466  if (strcmp(Binaries[BinaryCount]->DeviceTargetSpec,
1467  __SYCL_PI_DEVICE_BINARY_TARGET_UNKNOWN) == 0)
1468  UrBinaries[BinaryCount].pDeviceTargetSpec =
1469  UR_DEVICE_BINARY_TARGET_UNKNOWN;
1470  else if (strcmp(Binaries[BinaryCount]->DeviceTargetSpec,
1471  __SYCL_PI_DEVICE_BINARY_TARGET_SPIRV32) == 0)
1472  UrBinaries[BinaryCount].pDeviceTargetSpec =
1473  UR_DEVICE_BINARY_TARGET_SPIRV32;
1474  else if (strcmp(Binaries[BinaryCount]->DeviceTargetSpec,
1475  __SYCL_PI_DEVICE_BINARY_TARGET_SPIRV64) == 0)
1476  UrBinaries[BinaryCount].pDeviceTargetSpec =
1477  UR_DEVICE_BINARY_TARGET_SPIRV64;
1478  else if (strcmp(Binaries[BinaryCount]->DeviceTargetSpec,
1479  __SYCL_PI_DEVICE_BINARY_TARGET_SPIRV64_X86_64) == 0)
1480  UrBinaries[BinaryCount].pDeviceTargetSpec =
1481  UR_DEVICE_BINARY_TARGET_SPIRV64_X86_64;
1482  else if (strcmp(Binaries[BinaryCount]->DeviceTargetSpec,
1483  __SYCL_PI_DEVICE_BINARY_TARGET_SPIRV64_GEN) == 0)
1484  UrBinaries[BinaryCount].pDeviceTargetSpec =
1485  UR_DEVICE_BINARY_TARGET_SPIRV64_GEN;
1486  else if (strcmp(Binaries[BinaryCount]->DeviceTargetSpec,
1487  __SYCL_PI_DEVICE_BINARY_TARGET_SPIRV64_FPGA) == 0)
1488  UrBinaries[BinaryCount].pDeviceTargetSpec =
1489  UR_DEVICE_BINARY_TARGET_SPIRV64_FPGA;
1490  else if (strcmp(Binaries[BinaryCount]->DeviceTargetSpec,
1491  __SYCL_PI_DEVICE_BINARY_TARGET_NVPTX64) == 0)
1492  UrBinaries[BinaryCount].pDeviceTargetSpec =
1493  UR_DEVICE_BINARY_TARGET_NVPTX64;
1494  else if (strcmp(Binaries[BinaryCount]->DeviceTargetSpec,
1495  __SYCL_PI_DEVICE_BINARY_TARGET_AMDGCN) == 0)
1496  UrBinaries[BinaryCount].pDeviceTargetSpec =
1497  UR_DEVICE_BINARY_TARGET_AMDGCN;
1498  else if (strcmp(Binaries[BinaryCount]->DeviceTargetSpec,
1499  __SYCL_PI_DEVICE_BINARY_TARGET_NATIVE_CPU) == 0)
1500  UrBinaries[BinaryCount].pDeviceTargetSpec =
1501  "native_cpu"; // todo: define UR_DEVICE_BINARY_TARGET_NATIVE_CPU;
1502  else
1503  UrBinaries[BinaryCount].pDeviceTargetSpec =
1504  UR_DEVICE_BINARY_TARGET_UNKNOWN;
1505  }
1506 
1507  HANDLE_ERRORS(urDeviceSelectBinary(UrDevice, UrBinaries.data(), NumBinaries,
1508  SelectedBinaryInd));
1509  return PI_SUCCESS;
1510 }

1572  reinterpret_cast<const ur_device_handle_t *>(Devices);

1585 inline pi_result piContextGetInfo(pi_context Context, pi_context_info ParamName,
1586  size_t ParamValueSize, void *ParamValue,
1587  size_t *ParamValueSizeRet) {
1588 
1589  PI_ASSERT(Context, PI_ERROR_INVALID_CONTEXT);
1590 
1591  ur_context_handle_t hContext = reinterpret_cast<ur_context_handle_t>(Context);
1592  ur_context_info_t ContextInfoType{};
1593 
1594  switch (ParamName) {
1595  case PI_CONTEXT_INFO_DEVICES: {
1596  ContextInfoType = UR_CONTEXT_INFO_DEVICES;
1597  break;
1598  }
1599  case PI_CONTEXT_INFO_NUM_DEVICES: {
1600  ContextInfoType = UR_CONTEXT_INFO_NUM_DEVICES;
1601  break;
1602  }
1603  case PI_CONTEXT_INFO_REFERENCE_COUNT: {
1604  ContextInfoType = UR_CONTEXT_INFO_REFERENCE_COUNT;
1605  break;
1606  }
1607  case PI_EXT_ONEAPI_CONTEXT_INFO_USM_FILL2D_SUPPORT:
1608  case PI_EXT_ONEAPI_CONTEXT_INFO_USM_MEMSET2D_SUPPORT: {
1609  ContextInfoType = UR_CONTEXT_INFO_USM_FILL2D_SUPPORT;
1610  break;
1611  }
1612  case PI_EXT_ONEAPI_CONTEXT_INFO_USM_MEMCPY2D_SUPPORT: {
1613  ContextInfoType = UR_CONTEXT_INFO_USM_MEMCPY2D_SUPPORT;
1614  break;
1615  }
1616  case PI_EXT_CONTEXT_INFO_ATOMIC_MEMORY_ORDER_CAPABILITIES:
1617  case PI_EXT_CONTEXT_INFO_ATOMIC_MEMORY_SCOPE_CAPABILITIES:
1618  case PI_EXT_CONTEXT_INFO_ATOMIC_FENCE_ORDER_CAPABILITIES:
1619  case PI_EXT_CONTEXT_INFO_ATOMIC_FENCE_SCOPE_CAPABILITIES: {
1620  // These queries should be dealt with in context_impl.cpp by calling the
1621  // queries of each device separately and building the intersection set.
1622  die("These queries should have never come here");
1623  }
1624  default: {
1625  die("piContextGetInfo: unsuppported ParamName.");
1626  }
1627  }
1628 
1629  size_t UrParamValueSizeRet;
1630  HANDLE_ERRORS(urContextGetInfo(hContext, ContextInfoType, ParamValueSize,
1631  ParamValue, &UrParamValueSizeRet));
1632  if (ParamValueSizeRet) {
1633  *ParamValueSizeRet = UrParamValueSizeRet;
1634  }
1635  fixupInfoValueTypes(UrParamValueSizeRet, ParamValueSizeRet, ParamValueSize,
1636  ParamValue);
1637  return PI_SUCCESS;
1638 }

1658 // Queue
1659 inline pi_result piextQueueCreate(pi_context Context, pi_device Device,
1660  pi_queue_properties *Properties,
1661  pi_queue *Queue) {
1662 
1663  PI_ASSERT(Properties, PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE);
1664  // Expect flags mask to be passed first.
1665  PI_ASSERT(Properties[0] == PI_QUEUE_FLAGS, PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE);
1666 
1667  PI_ASSERT(Properties[2] == 0 ||
1668  (Properties[2] == PI_QUEUE_COMPUTE_INDEX && Properties[4] == 0),
1669  PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE);
1670 
1671  // Check that unexpected bits are not set.
1672  PI_ASSERT(!(Properties[1] &
1673  ~(PI_QUEUE_FLAG_OUT_OF_ORDER_EXEC_MODE_ENABLE |
1674  PI_QUEUE_FLAG_PROFILING_ENABLE | PI_QUEUE_FLAG_ON_DEVICE |
1675  PI_QUEUE_FLAG_ON_DEVICE_DEFAULT |
1676  PI_EXT_ONEAPI_QUEUE_FLAG_DISCARD_EVENTS |
1677  PI_EXT_ONEAPI_QUEUE_FLAG_PRIORITY_LOW |
1678  PI_EXT_ONEAPI_QUEUE_FLAG_PRIORITY_HIGH |
1679  PI_EXT_QUEUE_FLAG_SUBMISSION_NO_IMMEDIATE |
1680  PI_EXT_QUEUE_FLAG_SUBMISSION_IMMEDIATE)),
1681  PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE);
1682 
1683  PI_ASSERT(Context, PI_ERROR_INVALID_CONTEXT);
1684  PI_ASSERT(Queue, PI_ERROR_INVALID_QUEUE);
1685  PI_ASSERT(Device, PI_ERROR_INVALID_DEVICE);
1686 
1687  ur_queue_properties_t UrProperties{};
1688  UrProperties.stype = UR_STRUCTURE_TYPE_QUEUE_PROPERTIES;
1689  if (Properties[1] & PI_QUEUE_FLAG_OUT_OF_ORDER_EXEC_MODE_ENABLE)
1690  UrProperties.flags |= UR_QUEUE_FLAG_OUT_OF_ORDER_EXEC_MODE_ENABLE;
1691  if (Properties[1] & PI_QUEUE_FLAG_PROFILING_ENABLE)
1692  UrProperties.flags |= UR_QUEUE_FLAG_PROFILING_ENABLE;
1693  if (Properties[1] & PI_QUEUE_FLAG_ON_DEVICE)
1694  UrProperties.flags |= UR_QUEUE_FLAG_ON_DEVICE;
1695  if (Properties[1] & PI_QUEUE_FLAG_ON_DEVICE_DEFAULT)
1696  UrProperties.flags |= UR_QUEUE_FLAG_ON_DEVICE_DEFAULT;
1697  if (Properties[1] & PI_EXT_ONEAPI_QUEUE_FLAG_DISCARD_EVENTS)
1698  UrProperties.flags |= UR_QUEUE_FLAG_DISCARD_EVENTS;
1699  if (Properties[1] & PI_EXT_ONEAPI_QUEUE_FLAG_PRIORITY_LOW)
1700  UrProperties.flags |= UR_QUEUE_FLAG_PRIORITY_LOW;
1701  if (Properties[1] & PI_EXT_ONEAPI_QUEUE_FLAG_PRIORITY_HIGH)
1702  UrProperties.flags |= UR_QUEUE_FLAG_PRIORITY_HIGH;
1703  if (Properties[1] & __SYCL_PI_CUDA_SYNC_WITH_DEFAULT)
1704  UrProperties.flags |= UR_QUEUE_FLAG_SYNC_WITH_DEFAULT_STREAM;
1705  if (Properties[1] & __SYCL_PI_CUDA_USE_DEFAULT_STREAM)
1706  UrProperties.flags |= UR_QUEUE_FLAG_USE_DEFAULT_STREAM;
1707  if (Properties[1] & PI_EXT_QUEUE_FLAG_SUBMISSION_NO_IMMEDIATE)
1708  UrProperties.flags |= UR_QUEUE_FLAG_SUBMISSION_BATCHED;
1709  if (Properties[1] & PI_EXT_QUEUE_FLAG_SUBMISSION_IMMEDIATE)
1710  UrProperties.flags |= UR_QUEUE_FLAG_SUBMISSION_IMMEDIATE;
1711 
1712  ur_queue_index_properties_t IndexProperties{};
1713  IndexProperties.stype = UR_STRUCTURE_TYPE_QUEUE_INDEX_PROPERTIES;
1714  if (Properties[2] != 0) {
1715  IndexProperties.computeIndex = Properties[3];
1716  }
1717 
1718  UrProperties.pNext = &IndexProperties;
1719 
1720  ur_context_handle_t UrContext =
1721  reinterpret_cast<ur_context_handle_t>(Context);
1722  auto UrDevice = reinterpret_cast<ur_device_handle_t>(Device);
1723 
1724  ur_queue_handle_t *UrQueue = reinterpret_cast<ur_queue_handle_t *>(Queue);
1725  HANDLE_ERRORS(urQueueCreate(UrContext, UrDevice, &UrProperties, UrQueue));
1726 
1727  return PI_SUCCESS;
1728 }
1729 
1730 inline pi_result piQueueCreate(pi_context Context, pi_device Device,
1731  pi_queue_properties Flags, pi_queue *Queue) {
1732  pi_queue_properties Properties[] = {PI_QUEUE_FLAGS, Flags, 0};
1733  return pi2ur::piextQueueCreate(Context, Device, Properties, Queue);
1734 }

1736 inline pi_result piextQueueCreateWithNativeHandle(
1737  pi_native_handle NativeHandle, int32_t NativeHandleDesc, pi_context Context,
1738  pi_device Device, bool OwnNativeHandle, pi_queue_properties *Properties,
1739  pi_queue *Queue) {
1740  PI_ASSERT(Context, PI_ERROR_INVALID_CONTEXT);
1741  PI_ASSERT(NativeHandle, PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE);
1742  PI_ASSERT(Queue, PI_ERROR_INVALID_QUEUE);
1743 
1744  ur_context_handle_t UrContext =
1745  reinterpret_cast<ur_context_handle_t>(Context);
1746  ur_device_handle_t UrDevice = reinterpret_cast<ur_device_handle_t>(Device);
1747  ur_native_handle_t UrNativeHandle =
1748  reinterpret_cast<ur_native_handle_t>(NativeHandle);
1749  ur_queue_handle_t *UrQueue = reinterpret_cast<ur_queue_handle_t *>(Queue);
1750  ur_queue_native_properties_t UrNativeProperties{};
1751  UrNativeProperties.isNativeHandleOwned = OwnNativeHandle;
1752 
1753  ur_queue_properties_t UrProperties{};
1754  UrProperties.stype = UR_STRUCTURE_TYPE_QUEUE_PROPERTIES;
1755  if (Properties[1] & PI_QUEUE_FLAG_OUT_OF_ORDER_EXEC_MODE_ENABLE)
1756  UrProperties.flags |= UR_QUEUE_FLAG_OUT_OF_ORDER_EXEC_MODE_ENABLE;
1757  if (Properties[1] & PI_QUEUE_FLAG_PROFILING_ENABLE)
1758  UrProperties.flags |= UR_QUEUE_FLAG_PROFILING_ENABLE;
1759  if (Properties[1] & PI_QUEUE_FLAG_ON_DEVICE)
1760  UrProperties.flags |= UR_QUEUE_FLAG_ON_DEVICE;
1761  if (Properties[1] & PI_QUEUE_FLAG_ON_DEVICE_DEFAULT)
1762  UrProperties.flags |= UR_QUEUE_FLAG_ON_DEVICE_DEFAULT;
1763  if (Properties[1] & PI_EXT_ONEAPI_QUEUE_FLAG_DISCARD_EVENTS)
1764  UrProperties.flags |= UR_QUEUE_FLAG_DISCARD_EVENTS;
1765  if (Properties[1] & PI_EXT_ONEAPI_QUEUE_FLAG_PRIORITY_LOW)
1766  UrProperties.flags |= UR_QUEUE_FLAG_PRIORITY_LOW;
1767  if (Properties[1] & PI_EXT_ONEAPI_QUEUE_FLAG_PRIORITY_HIGH)
1768  UrProperties.flags |= UR_QUEUE_FLAG_PRIORITY_HIGH;
1769 
1770  ur_queue_native_desc_t UrNativeDesc{};
1771  UrNativeDesc.stype = UR_STRUCTURE_TYPE_QUEUE_NATIVE_DESC;
1772  UrNativeDesc.pNativeData = &NativeHandleDesc;
1773 
1774  UrProperties.pNext = &UrNativeDesc;
1775  UrNativeProperties.pNext = &UrProperties;
1776 
1777  HANDLE_ERRORS(urQueueCreateWithNativeHandle(
1778  UrNativeHandle, UrContext, UrDevice, &UrNativeProperties, UrQueue));
1779  return PI_SUCCESS;
1780 }

1901 inline pi_result piProgramCreate(pi_context Context, const void *ILBytes,
1902  size_t Length, pi_program *Program) {
1903 
1904  PI_ASSERT(Context, PI_ERROR_INVALID_CONTEXT);
1905  PI_ASSERT(ILBytes && Length, PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE);
1906  PI_ASSERT(Program, PI_ERROR_INVALID_PROGRAM);
1907 
1908  ur_context_handle_t UrContext =
1909  reinterpret_cast<ur_context_handle_t>(Context);
1910 
1911  ur_program_properties_t UrProperties{};
1912  ur_program_handle_t *UrProgram =
1913  reinterpret_cast<ur_program_handle_t *>(Program);
1914  HANDLE_ERRORS(urProgramCreateWithIL(UrContext, ILBytes, Length, &UrProperties,
1915  UrProgram));
1916 
1917  return PI_SUCCESS;
1918 }
1919 
1920 inline pi_result piProgramCreateWithBinary(
1921  pi_context Context, pi_uint32 NumDevices, const pi_device *DeviceList,
1922  const size_t *Lengths, const unsigned char **Binaries,
1923  size_t NumMetadataEntries, const pi_device_binary_property *Metadata,
1924  pi_int32 *BinaryStatus, pi_program *Program) {
1925  PI_ASSERT(Context, PI_ERROR_INVALID_CONTEXT);
1926  PI_ASSERT(DeviceList && NumDevices, PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE);
1927  PI_ASSERT(Binaries && Lengths, PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE);
1928  PI_ASSERT(Program, PI_ERROR_INVALID_PROGRAM);
1929 
1930  if (!Binaries[0] || !Lengths[0]) {
1931  if (BinaryStatus)
1932  *BinaryStatus = PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE;
1933  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE;
1934  }
1935 
1936  ur_context_handle_t UrContext =
1937  reinterpret_cast<ur_context_handle_t>(Context);
1938  auto UrDevice = reinterpret_cast<ur_device_handle_t>(DeviceList[0]);
1939 
1940  ur_program_properties_t Properties = {};
1941  Properties.stype = UR_STRUCTURE_TYPE_PROGRAM_PROPERTIES;
1942  Properties.pNext = nullptr;
1943  Properties.count = NumMetadataEntries;
1944 
1945  std::unique_ptr<ur_program_metadata_t[]> pMetadatas;
1946  if (NumMetadataEntries) {
1947  pMetadatas.reset(new ur_program_metadata_t[NumMetadataEntries]);
1948  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumMetadataEntries; i++) {
1949  HANDLE_ERRORS(mapPIMetadataToUR(&Metadata[i], &pMetadatas[i]));
1950  }
1951 
1952  Properties.pMetadatas = pMetadatas.get();
1953  }
1954 
1955  ur_program_handle_t *UrProgram =
1956  reinterpret_cast<ur_program_handle_t *>(Program);
1957  HANDLE_ERRORS(urProgramCreateWithBinary(UrContext, UrDevice, Lengths[0],
1958  Binaries[0], &Properties, UrProgram));
1959 
1960  if (BinaryStatus)
1961  *BinaryStatus = PI_SUCCESS;
1962 
1963  return PI_SUCCESS;
1964 }
1965 
1966 inline pi_result piProgramGetInfo(pi_program Program, pi_program_info ParamName,
1967  size_t ParamValueSize, void *ParamValue,
1968  size_t *ParamValueSizeRet) {
1969 
1970  PI_ASSERT(Program, PI_ERROR_INVALID_PROGRAM);
1971 
1972  ur_program_handle_t UrProgram =
1973  reinterpret_cast<ur_program_handle_t>(Program);
1974 
1975  ur_program_info_t PropName{};
1976 
1977  switch (ParamName) {
1978  case PI_PROGRAM_INFO_REFERENCE_COUNT: {
1979  PropName = UR_PROGRAM_INFO_REFERENCE_COUNT;
1980  break;
1981  }
1982  case PI_PROGRAM_INFO_CONTEXT: {
1983  PropName = UR_PROGRAM_INFO_CONTEXT;
1984  break;
1985  }
1986  case PI_PROGRAM_INFO_NUM_DEVICES: {
1987  PropName = UR_PROGRAM_INFO_NUM_DEVICES;
1988  break;
1989  }
1990  case PI_PROGRAM_INFO_DEVICES: {
1991  PropName = UR_PROGRAM_INFO_DEVICES;
1992  break;
1993  }
1994  case PI_PROGRAM_INFO_SOURCE: {
1995  PropName = UR_PROGRAM_INFO_SOURCE;
1996  break;
1997  }
1998  case PI_PROGRAM_INFO_BINARY_SIZES: {
1999  PropName = UR_PROGRAM_INFO_BINARY_SIZES;
2000  break;
2001  }
2002  case PI_PROGRAM_INFO_BINARIES: {
2003  PropName = UR_PROGRAM_INFO_BINARIES;
2004  break;
2005  }
2006  case PI_PROGRAM_INFO_NUM_KERNELS: {
2007  PropName = UR_PROGRAM_INFO_NUM_KERNELS;
2008  break;
2009  }
2010  case PI_PROGRAM_INFO_KERNEL_NAMES: {
2011  PropName = UR_PROGRAM_INFO_KERNEL_NAMES;
2012  break;
2013  }
2014  default: {
2015  die("urProgramGetInfo: not implemented");
2016  }
2017  }
2018 
2019  HANDLE_ERRORS(urProgramGetInfo(UrProgram, PropName, ParamValueSize,
2020  ParamValue, ParamValueSizeRet));
2021 
2022  return PI_SUCCESS;
2023 }
2024 
2025 inline pi_result
2026 piProgramLink(pi_context Context, pi_uint32 NumDevices,
2027  const pi_device *DeviceList, const char *Options,
2028  pi_uint32 NumInputPrograms, const pi_program *InputPrograms,
2029  void (*PFnNotify)(pi_program Program, void *UserData),
2030  void *UserData, pi_program *RetProgram) {
2031 
2032  // Validate input parameters.
2033  PI_ASSERT(DeviceList, PI_ERROR_INVALID_DEVICE);
2034  PI_ASSERT(!PFnNotify && !UserData, PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE);
2035  if (NumInputPrograms == 0 || InputPrograms == nullptr)
2036  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE;
2037 
2038  ur_context_handle_t UrContext =
2039  reinterpret_cast<ur_context_handle_t>(Context);
2040  const ur_program_handle_t *UrInputPrograms =
2041  reinterpret_cast<const ur_program_handle_t *>(InputPrograms);
2042  ur_program_handle_t *UrProgram =
2043  reinterpret_cast<ur_program_handle_t *>(RetProgram);
2044 
2045  auto UrDevices = reinterpret_cast<ur_device_handle_t *>(
2046  const_cast<pi_device *>(DeviceList));
2047 
2048  auto urResult =
2049  urProgramLinkExp(UrContext, NumDevices, UrDevices, NumInputPrograms,
2050  UrInputPrograms, Options, UrProgram);
2051  if (urResult == UR_RESULT_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_FEATURE) {
2052  urResult = urProgramLink(UrContext, NumInputPrograms, UrInputPrograms,
2053  Options, UrProgram);
2054  }
2055  return ur2piResult(urResult);
2056 }
2057 
2058 inline pi_result piProgramCompile(
2059  pi_program Program, pi_uint32 NumDevices, const pi_device *DeviceList,
2060  const char *Options, pi_uint32 NumInputHeaders,
2061  const pi_program *InputHeaders, const char **HeaderIncludeNames,
2062  void (*PFnNotify)(pi_program Program, void *UserData), void *UserData) {
2063 
2064  std::ignore = NumInputHeaders;
2065  std::ignore = InputHeaders;
2066  std::ignore = HeaderIncludeNames;
2067 
2068  PI_ASSERT(Program, PI_ERROR_INVALID_PROGRAM);
2069 
2070  if ((NumDevices && !DeviceList) || (!NumDevices && DeviceList))
2071  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE;
2072 
2073  // These aren't supported.
2074  PI_ASSERT(!PFnNotify && !UserData, PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE);
2075 
2076  ur_program_handle_t UrProgram =
2077  reinterpret_cast<ur_program_handle_t>(Program);
2078 
2079  ur_program_info_t PropName = UR_PROGRAM_INFO_CONTEXT;
2080  ur_context_handle_t UrContext{};
2081  HANDLE_ERRORS(urProgramGetInfo(UrProgram, PropName, sizeof(&UrContext),
2082  &UrContext, nullptr));
2083 
2084  auto UrDevices = reinterpret_cast<ur_device_handle_t *>(
2085  const_cast<pi_device *>(DeviceList));
2086 
2087  auto urResult =
2088  urProgramCompileExp(UrProgram, NumDevices, UrDevices, Options);
2089  if (urResult == UR_RESULT_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_FEATURE) {
2090  urResult = urProgramCompile(UrContext, UrProgram, Options);
2091  }
2092  return ur2piResult(urResult);
2093 }

2212 
2213 // Special version of piKernelSetArg to accept pi_mem.
2214 inline pi_result
2215 piextKernelSetArgMemObj(pi_kernel Kernel, pi_uint32 ArgIndex,
2216  const pi_mem_obj_property *ArgProperties,
2217  const pi_mem *ArgValue) {
2218 
2219  // TODO: the better way would probably be to add a new PI API for
2220  // extracting native PI object from PI handle, and have SYCL
2221  // RT pass that directly to the regular piKernelSetArg (and
2222  // then remove this piextKernelSetArgMemObj).
2223 
2224  PI_ASSERT(Kernel, PI_ERROR_INVALID_KERNEL);
2225 
2226  ur_mem_handle_t UrMemory{};
2227  if (ArgValue)
2228  UrMemory = reinterpret_cast<ur_mem_handle_t>(*ArgValue);
2229 
2230  // We don't yet know the device where this kernel will next be run on.
2231  // Thus we can't know the actual memory allocation that needs to be used.
2232  // Remember the memory object being used as an argument for this kernel
2233  // to process it later when the device is known (at the kernel enqueue).
2234  //
2235  ur_kernel_handle_t UrKernel = reinterpret_cast<ur_kernel_handle_t>(Kernel);
2236  // the only applicable type, just ignore anything else
2237  if (ArgProperties && ArgProperties->type == PI_KERNEL_ARG_MEM_OBJ_ACCESS) {
2238  // following structure layout checks to be replaced with
2239  // std::is_layout_compatible after move to C++20
2240  static_assert(sizeof(pi_mem_obj_property) ==
2241  sizeof(ur_kernel_arg_mem_obj_properties_t));
2242  static_assert(sizeof(pi_mem_obj_property::type) ==
2243  sizeof(ur_kernel_arg_mem_obj_properties_t::stype));
2244  static_assert(sizeof(pi_mem_obj_property::pNext) ==
2245  sizeof(ur_kernel_arg_mem_obj_properties_t::pNext));
2246  static_assert(sizeof(pi_mem_obj_property::mem_access) ==
2247  sizeof(ur_kernel_arg_mem_obj_properties_t::memoryAccess));
2248 
2249  static_assert(uint32_t(PI_ACCESS_READ_WRITE) ==
2250  uint32_t(UR_MEM_FLAG_READ_WRITE));
2251  static_assert(uint32_t(PI_ACCESS_READ_ONLY) ==
2252  uint32_t(UR_MEM_FLAG_READ_ONLY));
2253  static_assert(uint32_t(PI_ACCESS_WRITE_ONLY) ==
2254  uint32_t(UR_MEM_FLAG_WRITE_ONLY));
2255  static_assert(uint32_t(PI_KERNEL_ARG_MEM_OBJ_ACCESS) ==
2256  uint32_t(UR_STRUCTURE_TYPE_KERNEL_ARG_MEM_OBJ_PROPERTIES));
2257 
2258  const ur_kernel_arg_mem_obj_properties_t *UrMemProperties =
2259  reinterpret_cast<const ur_kernel_arg_mem_obj_properties_t *>(
2260  ArgProperties);
2261  HANDLE_ERRORS(
2262  urKernelSetArgMemObj(UrKernel, ArgIndex, UrMemProperties, UrMemory));
2263  } else {
2264  HANDLE_ERRORS(urKernelSetArgMemObj(UrKernel, ArgIndex, nullptr, UrMemory));
2265  }
2266 
2267  return PI_SUCCESS;
2268 }
2269

2328 inline pi_result piKernelSetExecInfo(pi_kernel Kernel,
2329  pi_kernel_exec_info ParamName,
2330  size_t ParamValueSize,
2331  const void *ParamValue) {
2332 
2333  PI_ASSERT(Kernel, PI_ERROR_INVALID_KERNEL);
2334  PI_ASSERT(ParamValue, PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE);
2335 
2336  ur_kernel_handle_t UrKernel = reinterpret_cast<ur_kernel_handle_t>(Kernel);
2337  ur_kernel_exec_info_t PropName{};
2338  uint64_t PropValue{};
2339  switch (ParamName) {
2340  case PI_USM_INDIRECT_ACCESS: {
2341  PropName = UR_KERNEL_EXEC_INFO_USM_INDIRECT_ACCESS;
2342  PropValue = *(static_cast<uint64_t *>(const_cast<void *>(ParamValue)));
2343  break;
2344  }
2345  case PI_USM_PTRS: {
2346  PropName = UR_KERNEL_EXEC_INFO_USM_PTRS;
2347  break;
2348  }
2349  case PI_EXT_KERNEL_EXEC_INFO_CACHE_CONFIG: {
2350  PropName = UR_KERNEL_EXEC_INFO_CACHE_CONFIG;
2351  auto Param = (*(static_cast<const pi_kernel_cache_config *>(ParamValue)));
2352  if (Param == PI_EXT_KERNEL_EXEC_INFO_CACHE_LARGE_SLM) {
2353  PropValue = static_cast<uint64_t>(UR_KERNEL_CACHE_CONFIG_LARGE_SLM);
2354  } else if (Param == PI_EXT_KERNEL_EXEC_INFO_CACHE_LARGE_DATA) {
2355  PropValue = static_cast<uint64_t>(UR_KERNEL_CACHE_CONFIG_LARGE_DATA);
2356  break;
2357  } else if (Param == PI_EXT_KERNEL_EXEC_INFO_CACHE_DEFAULT) {
2358  PropValue = static_cast<uint64_t>(UR_KERNEL_CACHE_CONFIG_DEFAULT);
2359  } else {
2360  die("piKernelSetExecInfo: unsupported ParamValue\n");
2361  }
2362  break;
2363  }
2364  default:
2365  die("piKernelSetExecInfo: unsupported ParamName\n");
2366  }
2367  HANDLE_ERRORS(urKernelSetExecInfo(UrKernel, PropName, ParamValueSize, nullptr,
2368  &PropValue));
2369 
2370  return PI_SUCCESS;
2371 }

2409 inline pi_result piKernelGetInfo(pi_kernel Kernel, pi_kernel_info ParamName,
2410  size_t ParamValueSize, void *ParamValue,
2411  size_t *ParamValueSizeRet) {
2412  PI_ASSERT(Kernel, PI_ERROR_INVALID_KERNEL);
2413 
2414  ur_kernel_handle_t UrKernel = reinterpret_cast<ur_kernel_handle_t>(Kernel);
2415  ur_kernel_info_t UrParamName{};
2416  switch (ParamName) {
2417  case PI_KERNEL_INFO_FUNCTION_NAME: {
2418  UrParamName = UR_KERNEL_INFO_FUNCTION_NAME;
2419  break;
2420  }
2421  case PI_KERNEL_INFO_NUM_ARGS: {
2422  size_t NumArgs = 0;
2423  HANDLE_ERRORS(urKernelGetInfo(UrKernel, UR_KERNEL_INFO_NUM_ARGS,
2424  sizeof(NumArgs), &NumArgs, nullptr));
2425  if (ParamValueSizeRet) {
2426  *ParamValueSizeRet = sizeof(uint32_t);
2427  }
2428  if (ParamValue) {
2429  if (ParamValueSize != sizeof(uint32_t))
2430  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_BUFFER_SIZE;
2431  *static_cast<uint32_t *>(ParamValue) = static_cast<uint32_t>(NumArgs);
2432  }
2433  return PI_SUCCESS;
2434  }
2435  case PI_KERNEL_INFO_REFERENCE_COUNT: {
2436  UrParamName = UR_KERNEL_INFO_REFERENCE_COUNT;
2437  break;
2438  }
2439  case PI_KERNEL_INFO_CONTEXT: {
2440  UrParamName = UR_KERNEL_INFO_CONTEXT;
2441  break;
2442  }
2443  case PI_KERNEL_INFO_PROGRAM: {
2444  UrParamName = UR_KERNEL_INFO_PROGRAM;
2445  break;
2446  }
2447  case PI_KERNEL_INFO_ATTRIBUTES: {
2448  UrParamName = UR_KERNEL_INFO_ATTRIBUTES;
2449  break;
2450  }
2451  default:
2452  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_PROPERTY;
2453  }
2454 
2455  HANDLE_ERRORS(urKernelGetInfo(UrKernel, UrParamName, ParamValueSize,
2456  ParamValue, ParamValueSizeRet));
2457 
2458  return PI_SUCCESS;
2459 }

2461 inline pi_result piKernelGetGroupInfo(pi_kernel Kernel, pi_device Device,
2462  pi_kernel_group_info ParamName,
2463  size_t ParamValueSize, void *ParamValue,
2464  size_t *ParamValueSizeRet) {

2474  UrParamName = UR_KERNEL_GROUP_INFO_GLOBAL_WORK_SIZE;
2475  break;
2476  }
2477  case PI_KERNEL_GROUP_INFO_WORK_GROUP_SIZE: {
2478  UrParamName = UR_KERNEL_GROUP_INFO_WORK_GROUP_SIZE;

2511  ParamValueSize, ParamValue,
2512  ParamValueSizeRet));

2596 inline pi_result piProgramGetBuildInfo(pi_program Program, pi_device Device,

2598  size_t ParamValueSize, void *ParamValue,
2599  size_t *ParamValueSizeRet) {
2600 
2601  ur_program_handle_t UrProgram =
2602  reinterpret_cast<ur_program_handle_t>(Program);
2603  auto UrDevice = reinterpret_cast<ur_device_handle_t>(Device);
2604 
2605  ur_program_build_info_t PropName{};
2606  switch (ParamName) {
2607  case PI_PROGRAM_BUILD_INFO_STATUS: {
2608  PropName = UR_PROGRAM_BUILD_INFO_STATUS;
2609  break;
2610  }
2611  case PI_PROGRAM_BUILD_INFO_OPTIONS: {
2612  PropName = UR_PROGRAM_BUILD_INFO_OPTIONS;
2613  break;
2614  }
2615  case PI_PROGRAM_BUILD_INFO_LOG: {
2616  PropName = UR_PROGRAM_BUILD_INFO_LOG;
2617  break;
2618  }
2619  case PI_PROGRAM_BUILD_INFO_BINARY_TYPE: {
2620  PropName = UR_PROGRAM_BUILD_INFO_BINARY_TYPE;
2621  break;
2622  }
2623  default: {
2624  die("piProgramGetBuildInfo: not implemented");
2625  }
2626  }
2627 
2628  size_t SizeInOut = ParamValueSize;
2629  HANDLE_ERRORS(urProgramGetBuildInfo(UrProgram, UrDevice, PropName,
2630  ParamValueSize, ParamValue,
2631  ParamValueSizeRet));
2632  ur2piProgramBuildInfoValue(PropName, ParamValueSize, &SizeInOut, ParamValue);
2633  return PI_SUCCESS;
2634 }

2730 // Program
2732 
2734 // Memory
2735 inline pi_result piMemBufferCreate(pi_context Context, pi_mem_flags Flags,
2736  size_t Size, void *HostPtr, pi_mem *RetMem,
2737  const pi_mem_properties *properties) {
2738 
2739  PI_ASSERT(Context, PI_ERROR_INVALID_CONTEXT);
2740  PI_ASSERT(RetMem, PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE);
2741 
2742  ur_context_handle_t UrContext =
2743  reinterpret_cast<ur_context_handle_t>(Context);
2744 
2745  ur_mem_flags_t UrBufferFlags{};
2746  if (Flags & PI_MEM_FLAGS_ACCESS_RW) {
2747  UrBufferFlags |= UR_MEM_FLAG_READ_WRITE;
2748  }
2749  if (Flags & PI_MEM_ACCESS_READ_ONLY) {
2750  UrBufferFlags |= UR_MEM_FLAG_READ_ONLY;
2751  }
2752  if (Flags & PI_MEM_FLAGS_HOST_PTR_USE) {
2753  UrBufferFlags |= UR_MEM_FLAG_USE_HOST_POINTER;
2754  }
2755  if (Flags & PI_MEM_FLAGS_HOST_PTR_COPY) {
2756  UrBufferFlags |= UR_MEM_FLAG_ALLOC_COPY_HOST_POINTER;
2757  }
2758  if (Flags & PI_MEM_FLAGS_HOST_PTR_ALLOC) {
2759  UrBufferFlags |= UR_MEM_FLAG_ALLOC_HOST_POINTER;
2760  }
2761 
2762  ur_buffer_properties_t UrProps{};
2763  UrProps.stype = UR_STRUCTURE_TYPE_BUFFER_PROPERTIES;
2764  UrProps.pHost = HostPtr;
2765 
2766  ur_buffer_channel_properties_t bufferChannelProperties{};
2767  bufferChannelProperties.stype = UR_STRUCTURE_TYPE_BUFFER_CHANNEL_PROPERTIES;
2768  ur_buffer_alloc_location_properties_t bufferLocationProperties{};
2769  bufferLocationProperties.stype =
2770  UR_STRUCTURE_TYPE_BUFFER_ALLOC_LOCATION_PROPERTIES;
2771  if (properties != nullptr) {
2772  bool bufferLocationPropertySet = false;
2773  bool bufferMemChannelPropertySet = false;
2774  uint64_t allocBufferLocation = 0;
2775  uint32_t allocBufferMemChannel = 0;
2776  // pi mem properties must ended by 0
2777  size_t I = 0;
2778  while (properties[I] != 0) {
2779  if (properties[I] == PI_MEM_PROPERTIES_ALLOC_BUFFER_LOCATION) {
2780  allocBufferLocation = properties[I + 1];
2781  bufferLocationPropertySet = true;
2782  } else if (properties[I] == PI_MEM_PROPERTIES_CHANNEL) {
2783  allocBufferMemChannel = properties[I + 1];
2784  bufferMemChannelPropertySet = true;
2785  }
2786  I += 2;
2787  }
2788  void *extensionProperties = nullptr;
2789  if (bufferLocationPropertySet) {
2790  bufferLocationProperties.location = allocBufferLocation;
2791  extensionProperties = &bufferLocationProperties;
2792  }
2793  if (bufferMemChannelPropertySet) {
2794  bufferChannelProperties.channel = allocBufferMemChannel;
2795  extensionProperties = &bufferChannelProperties;
2796  }
2797  if (bufferLocationPropertySet && bufferMemChannelPropertySet) {
2798  bufferLocationProperties.pNext = &bufferChannelProperties;
2799  extensionProperties = &bufferLocationProperties;
2800  }
2801  UrProps.pNext = extensionProperties;
2802  }
2803  ur_mem_handle_t *UrBuffer = reinterpret_cast<ur_mem_handle_t *>(RetMem);
2804  HANDLE_ERRORS(
2805  urMemBufferCreate(UrContext, UrBufferFlags, Size, &UrProps, UrBuffer));
2806 
2807  return PI_SUCCESS;
2808 }
2809 
2810 inline pi_result piextUSMHostAlloc(void **ResultPtr, pi_context Context,
2811  pi_usm_mem_properties *Properties,
2812  size_t Size, pi_uint32 Alignment) {
2813  ur_usm_desc_t USMDesc{};
2814  USMDesc.align = Alignment;
2815 
2816  ur_usm_alloc_location_desc_t UsmLocationDesc{};
2817  UsmLocationDesc.stype = UR_STRUCTURE_TYPE_USM_ALLOC_LOCATION_DESC;
2818 
2819  if (Properties) {
2820  uint32_t Next = 0;
2821  while (Properties[Next]) {
2822  if (Properties[Next] == PI_MEM_USM_ALLOC_BUFFER_LOCATION) {
2823  UsmLocationDesc.location = static_cast<uint32_t>(Properties[Next + 1]);
2824  USMDesc.pNext = &UsmLocationDesc;
2825  } else {
2826  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE;
2827  }
2828  Next += 2;
2829  }
2830  }
2831 
2832  ur_context_handle_t UrContext =
2833  reinterpret_cast<ur_context_handle_t>(Context);
2834 
2835  ur_usm_pool_handle_t Pool{};
2836  HANDLE_ERRORS(urUSMHostAlloc(UrContext, &USMDesc, Pool, Size, ResultPtr));
2837  return PI_SUCCESS;
2838 }

3077 inline pi_result piMemImageCreate(pi_context Context, pi_mem_flags Flags,
3078  const pi_image_format *ImageFormat,
3079  const pi_image_desc *ImageDesc, void *HostPtr,
3080  pi_mem *RetImage) {
3081 
3082  PI_ASSERT(Context, PI_ERROR_INVALID_CONTEXT);
3083  PI_ASSERT(RetImage, PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE);
3084  PI_ASSERT(ImageFormat, PI_ERROR_INVALID_IMAGE_FORMAT_DESCRIPTOR);
3085 
3086  ur_context_handle_t UrContext =
3087  reinterpret_cast<ur_context_handle_t>(Context);
3088 
3089  ur_mem_flags_t UrFlags{};
3090  if (Flags & PI_MEM_FLAGS_ACCESS_RW) {
3091  UrFlags |= UR_MEM_FLAG_READ_WRITE;
3092  }
3093  if (Flags & PI_MEM_ACCESS_READ_ONLY) {
3094  UrFlags |= UR_MEM_FLAG_READ_ONLY;
3095  }
3096  if (Flags & PI_MEM_FLAGS_HOST_PTR_USE) {
3097  UrFlags |= UR_MEM_FLAG_USE_HOST_POINTER;

3148 inline pi_result piMemBufferPartition(pi_mem Buffer, pi_mem_flags Flags,
3149  pi_buffer_create_type BufferCreateType,
3150  void *BufferCreateInfo, pi_mem *RetMem) {
3151 
3152  PI_ASSERT(BufferCreateType == PI_BUFFER_CREATE_TYPE_REGION &&
3153  BufferCreateInfo && RetMem,
3154  PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE);
3155 
3156  auto Region = (pi_buffer_region)BufferCreateInfo;
3157  PI_ASSERT(Region->size != 0u, PI_ERROR_INVALID_BUFFER_SIZE);
3158  PI_ASSERT(Region->origin <= (Region->origin + Region->size),
3159  PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE);
3160 
3161  ur_mem_handle_t UrBuffer = reinterpret_cast<ur_mem_handle_t>(Buffer);
3162 
3163  ur_mem_flags_t UrFlags{};
3164  if (Flags & PI_MEM_FLAGS_ACCESS_RW) {
3165  UrFlags |= UR_MEM_FLAG_READ_WRITE;
3166  }
3167  if (Flags & PI_MEM_ACCESS_READ_ONLY) {
3168  UrFlags |= UR_MEM_FLAG_READ_ONLY;
3169  }
3170  if (Flags & PI_MEM_FLAGS_HOST_PTR_USE) {
3171  UrFlags |= UR_MEM_FLAG_USE_HOST_POINTER;
3172  }
3173  if (Flags & PI_MEM_FLAGS_HOST_PTR_COPY) {
3174  UrFlags |= UR_MEM_FLAG_ALLOC_COPY_HOST_POINTER;
3175  }
3176  if (Flags & PI_MEM_FLAGS_HOST_PTR_ALLOC) {
3177  UrFlags |= UR_MEM_FLAG_ALLOC_HOST_POINTER;
3178  }
3179 
3180  ur_buffer_create_type_t UrBufferCreateType{};
3181  if (BufferCreateType == PI_BUFFER_CREATE_TYPE_REGION) {
3182  UrBufferCreateType = UR_BUFFER_CREATE_TYPE_REGION;
3183  }
3184 
3185  ur_buffer_region_t UrBufferCreateInfo{};
3186  UrBufferCreateInfo.origin = Region->origin;
3187  UrBufferCreateInfo.size = Region->size;
3188  ur_mem_handle_t *UrMem = reinterpret_cast<ur_mem_handle_t *>(RetMem);
3189  HANDLE_ERRORS(urMemBufferPartition(UrBuffer, UrFlags, UrBufferCreateType,
3190  &UrBufferCreateInfo, UrMem));
3191 
3192  return PI_SUCCESS;
3193 }

3262 inline pi_result piextUSMDeviceAlloc(void **ResultPtr, pi_context Context,
3263  pi_device Device,
3264  pi_usm_mem_properties *Properties,
3265  size_t Size, pi_uint32 Alignment) {
3266  ur_context_handle_t UrContext =
3267  reinterpret_cast<ur_context_handle_t>(Context);
3268  auto UrDevice = reinterpret_cast<ur_device_handle_t>(Device);
3269 
3270  ur_usm_desc_t USMDesc{};
3271  USMDesc.align = Alignment;
3272 
3273  ur_usm_alloc_location_desc_t UsmLocDesc{};
3274  UsmLocDesc.stype = UR_STRUCTURE_TYPE_USM_ALLOC_LOCATION_DESC;
3275 
3276  if (Properties) {
3277  uint32_t Next = 0;
3278  while (Properties[Next]) {
3279  if (Properties[Next] == PI_MEM_USM_ALLOC_BUFFER_LOCATION) {
3280  UsmLocDesc.location = static_cast<uint32_t>(Properties[Next + 1]);
3281  USMDesc.pNext = &UsmLocDesc;
3282  } else {
3283  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE;
3284  }
3285  Next += 2;
3286  }
3287  }
3288 
3289  ur_usm_pool_handle_t Pool{};
3290  HANDLE_ERRORS(
3291  urUSMDeviceAlloc(UrContext, UrDevice, &USMDesc, Pool, Size, ResultPtr));
3292 
3293  return PI_SUCCESS;
3294 }

3300  unsigned int ElementSizeBytes) {

3305  auto UrDevice = reinterpret_cast<ur_device_handle_t>(Device);
3306  std::ignore = Properties;
3307  ur_usm_desc_t USMDesc{};
3308  ur_usm_pool_handle_t Pool{};
3309 
3310  HANDLE_ERRORS(urUSMPitchedAllocExp(UrContext, UrDevice, &USMDesc, Pool,

3317 inline pi_result piextUSMSharedAlloc(void **ResultPtr, pi_context Context,
3318  pi_device Device,
3319  pi_usm_mem_properties *Properties,
3320  size_t Size, pi_uint32 Alignment) {
3321  ur_context_handle_t UrContext =
3322  reinterpret_cast<ur_context_handle_t>(Context);
3323  auto UrDevice = reinterpret_cast<ur_device_handle_t>(Device);
3324 
3325  ur_usm_desc_t USMDesc{};
3326  USMDesc.align = Alignment;
3327  ur_usm_device_desc_t UsmDeviceDesc{};
3328  UsmDeviceDesc.stype = UR_STRUCTURE_TYPE_USM_DEVICE_DESC;
3329  ur_usm_host_desc_t UsmHostDesc{};
3330  UsmHostDesc.stype = UR_STRUCTURE_TYPE_USM_HOST_DESC;
3331  ur_usm_alloc_location_desc_t UsmLocationDesc{};
3332  UsmLocationDesc.stype = UR_STRUCTURE_TYPE_USM_ALLOC_LOCATION_DESC;
3333 
3334  // One properties bitfield can correspond to a host_desc and a device_desc
3335  // struct, since having `0` values in these is harmless we can set up this
3336  // pNext chain in advance.
3337  USMDesc.pNext = &UsmDeviceDesc;
3338  UsmDeviceDesc.pNext = &UsmHostDesc;
3339 
3340  if (Properties) {
3341  uint32_t Next = 0;
3342  while (Properties[Next]) {
3343  switch (Properties[Next]) {
3344  case PI_MEM_ALLOC_FLAGS: {
3345  if (Properties[Next + 1] & PI_MEM_ALLOC_WRTITE_COMBINED) {
3346  UsmDeviceDesc.flags |= UR_USM_DEVICE_MEM_FLAG_WRITE_COMBINED;
3347  }
3348  if (Properties[Next + 1] & PI_MEM_ALLOC_INITIAL_PLACEMENT_DEVICE) {
3349  UsmDeviceDesc.flags |= UR_USM_DEVICE_MEM_FLAG_INITIAL_PLACEMENT;
3350  }
3351  if (Properties[Next + 1] & PI_MEM_ALLOC_INITIAL_PLACEMENT_HOST) {
3352  UsmHostDesc.flags |= UR_USM_HOST_MEM_FLAG_INITIAL_PLACEMENT;
3353  }
3354  if (Properties[Next + 1] & PI_MEM_ALLOC_DEVICE_READ_ONLY) {
3355  UsmDeviceDesc.flags |= UR_USM_DEVICE_MEM_FLAG_DEVICE_READ_ONLY;
3356  }
3357  break;
3358  }
3359  case PI_MEM_USM_ALLOC_BUFFER_LOCATION: {
3360  UsmLocationDesc.location = static_cast<uint32_t>(Properties[Next + 1]);
3361  // We wait until we've seen a BUFFER_LOCATION property to tack this
3362  // onto the end of the chain, a `0` here might be valid as far as we
3363  // know so we must exclude it unless we've been given a value.
3364  UsmHostDesc.pNext = &UsmLocationDesc;
3365  break;
3366  }
3367  default:
3368  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE;
3369  }
3370  Next += 2;
3371  }
3372  }
3373 
3374  ur_usm_pool_handle_t Pool{};
3375  HANDLE_ERRORS(
3376  urUSMSharedAlloc(UrContext, UrDevice, &USMDesc, Pool, Size, ResultPtr));
3377 
3378  return PI_SUCCESS;
3379 }

3454 inline pi_result piextUSMEnqueueMemAdvise(pi_queue Queue, const void *Ptr,
3455  size_t Length, pi_mem_advice Advice,
3456  pi_event *OutEvent) {
3457 
3458  PI_ASSERT(Queue, PI_ERROR_INVALID_QUEUE);
3459 
3460  ur_queue_handle_t UrQueue = reinterpret_cast<ur_queue_handle_t>(Queue);
3461 
3462  ur_event_handle_t *UREvent = reinterpret_cast<ur_event_handle_t *>(OutEvent);
3463 
3464  ur_usm_advice_flags_t UrAdvice{};
3465  if (Advice & PI_MEM_ADVICE_CUDA_SET_READ_MOSTLY) {
3466  UrAdvice |= UR_USM_ADVICE_FLAG_SET_READ_MOSTLY;
3467  }
3468  if (Advice & PI_MEM_ADVICE_CUDA_UNSET_READ_MOSTLY) {
3469  UrAdvice |= UR_USM_ADVICE_FLAG_CLEAR_READ_MOSTLY;
3470  }
3471  if (Advice & PI_MEM_ADVICE_CUDA_SET_PREFERRED_LOCATION) {
3472  UrAdvice |= UR_USM_ADVICE_FLAG_SET_PREFERRED_LOCATION;
3473  }
3474  if (Advice & PI_MEM_ADVICE_CUDA_UNSET_PREFERRED_LOCATION) {
3475  UrAdvice |= UR_USM_ADVICE_FLAG_CLEAR_PREFERRED_LOCATION;
3476  }
3477  if (Advice & PI_MEM_ADVICE_CUDA_SET_ACCESSED_BY) {
3478  UrAdvice |= UR_USM_ADVICE_FLAG_SET_ACCESSED_BY_DEVICE;
3479  }
3480  if (Advice & PI_MEM_ADVICE_CUDA_UNSET_ACCESSED_BY) {
3481  UrAdvice |= UR_USM_ADVICE_FLAG_CLEAR_ACCESSED_BY_DEVICE;
3482  }
3483  if (Advice & PI_MEM_ADVICE_CUDA_SET_ACCESSED_BY_HOST) {
3484  UrAdvice |= UR_USM_ADVICE_FLAG_SET_ACCESSED_BY_HOST;
3485  }
3486  if (Advice & PI_MEM_ADVICE_CUDA_UNSET_ACCESSED_BY_HOST) {
3487  UrAdvice |= UR_USM_ADVICE_FLAG_CLEAR_ACCESSED_BY_HOST;
3488  }
3489  if (Advice & PI_MEM_ADVICE_HIP_SET_COARSE_GRAINED) {
3490  UrAdvice |= UR_USM_ADVICE_FLAG_SET_NON_COHERENT_MEMORY;
3491  }
3492  if (Advice & PI_MEM_ADVICE_HIP_UNSET_COARSE_GRAINED) {
3493  UrAdvice |= UR_USM_ADVICE_FLAG_CLEAR_NON_COHERENT_MEMORY;
3494  }
3495  if (Advice & PI_MEM_ADVICE_RESET) {
3496  UrAdvice |= UR_USM_ADVICE_FLAG_DEFAULT;
3497  }
3498 
3499  HANDLE_ERRORS(urEnqueueUSMAdvise(UrQueue, Ptr, Length, UrAdvice, UREvent));
3500 
3501  return PI_SUCCESS;
3502 }

3678 inline pi_result piextUSMEnqueueMemcpy2D(pi_queue Queue, pi_bool Blocking,
3679  void *DstPtr, size_t DstPitch,
3680  const void *SrcPtr, size_t SrcPitch,

3687  return PI_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE;

3693  reinterpret_cast<const ur_event_handle_t *>(EventsWaitList);
3694 
3695  ur_event_handle_t *UREvent = reinterpret_cast<ur_event_handle_t *>(OutEvent);
3696 
3697  HANDLE_ERRORS(urEnqueueUSMMemcpy2D(
3698  UrQueue, Blocking, DstPtr, DstPitch, SrcPtr, SrcPitch, Width, Height,
3699  NumEventsInWaitList, UrEventsWaitList, UREvent));
3700 
3701  return PI_SUCCESS;
3702 }

3815 inline pi_result piEnqueueMemBufferMap(
